<!-- Begin Content -->
<P>
Dear Aurum, Vault Network and IGN,<P>It has come to my attention that legal efforts are actively being made to correct an oversight when it comes to volunteer work.  Specifically, the counselors of Ultima Online have taken up litigation arms against Origin Systems and Electronic Arts in order to rectify a long-standing arrangement that exists to exploit those who are generous of their time and efforts.  It is only right that such kind-hearted souls be compensated for these qualities they extend to others, and I cannot help but notice several parallels between their situation and mine with EQ Vault.<P>When I was first approached as a contributing columnist, it was made clear to me that my work would better the community.  What was not made clear to me was the idea that the fruits of my labors would be used by a profit-making company to further their financial agenda.  Such a thing is exploitation, pure and simple.<P>I therefore submit that you must pay me <I>at least</I> the listed minimum wage of $5.15 per hour for the volunteer service I offer your web site, along with benefits such as medical coverage, 401K, stock options, free access to the Internet, the title of "Your Majesty," and a chocolate mint on my pillow every night as I go to bed.  Otherwise, like other similar companies in the media, you may very well be served a summons to court for back pay.<P>Furthermore, I must protest to the semi-automatic weapon that is consistently held to my head as I perform such duties for you.  Had I a choice in the matter, I would never have continued slaving away as your personal editorial writer for no money, sustenance or compensation of any kind.  I don't even get a free account with which to play the game, so I can comment (somewhat) intelligently on the topic of EverQuest.  Funding for such research comes from my own hard-earned money, and I'll not stand for it any longer.<P>In addition, I resent being used as a tool for your profits instead of being a part of building a greater community.  I resent writing article after article, knowing that what I do isn't truly enjoyable, contrary to my own feelings on the matter.  I resent being held hostage to your desire for wealth under the guise of being offered an opportunity to make a difference for people who read my material.  I resent the fact that, even though I may find fulfillment and joy in the work I do, that I have been taken advantage of by you greedy people.  Shame on you!  Shame, shame!<P>And therefore you must be made to suffer, and I must now reap hoards of cash so I can quit my day job and spend the bulk of my waking hours playing the game you endorse.  Know that Verant Interactive and 989 Studios will be receiving similar mail from me.  The time I spend playing EverQuest is, in fact, research time (tax deductible now that this is my career-of-choice), and I believe that I should be paid by them as well for the time I spend endorsing their product.  To do any less would be immoral and unjust, and cannot be tolerated in this great nation of ours.  As your contributing writer, I am now a part of the country's workforce, dammit, and I demand satisfaction for what I do.<P>Facetiously,<P>-&lt;Shadoe&gt;<P>(P.S: And I want a pony, too!)

