<SPAN CLASS="pagesub">Lanys T`Vyl: Her Return</SPAN><br>
<img src="/images/topback.jpg" valign="bottom" width=475 height=2><br>
<SPAN CLASS="credit">Author:</SPAN> 
<span class="credit2">Koori  (<a href="mailto:N/A" class="credit2">N/A</a>)</SPAN>&nbsp;&nbsp;  
<SPAN CLASS="credit">Organization:</SPAN> <a href="" class="credit2">Bristlebane Server</a><br>

<SPAN CLASS="regtext">
<!-- Begin Content -->
<P>
A tale must be told ....<br><br><b>CHECKMATE</b><br><br>It started out a normal day, well at least as normal as it gets for me. I<br>awoke under the veil of invisibility in the valley that runs between the<br>smoldering rocks of Lavastorm Mountains and the forest of my childhood,<br>Nektulos. Yes, you heard right ... I am Teir`Dal, but don't let my birth<br>name fool you for in my world everything is an illusion.<br><br>Anyway, back to the tale at hand. I awoke and readied myself for a trip to<br>my hometown, I would not be warmly welcomed but as long as the guards did<br>not notice my true self, I would be safe from the anger of the royal<br>family. I did not bother to summon my protector ... my daggers were few and<br>the woods was safe for me. I had just advanced to my eighteenth level of<br>skills .. was eager to see if my guild master may have new knowledge to<br>share with me and my daggers and the cat eye agates I needed for my Rune<br>spell were needed. It was for these reasons I chose to venture toward<br>Neriak.<br><br>As I neared the cavern guarding the Teir`Dal a shout was heard through out<br>the zone. Someone identifying herself as an Emissary to the Queen<br>Cristianos Thex, was asking for others to join her to bring in Lanys for<br>questioning by The Dead. Lanys T`Vyl? Innoruuk's Daughter? I have no love<br>for either god nor daughter but perhaps the child in me was wondering for I<br>followed the cry to find this Emissary standing before the city.<br><br>By the time I got there a small crowd had gathered. Staying hidden from<br>view I listened as the Emissary D`Veiu explained that Lanys was not to be<br>harmed only brought in for questioning. I could see in the other's eyes<br>this was a lie .. but was not sure of the truth. The Emissary then asked<br>all of those who were loyal to The Dead to assist in Lanys's apprehension.<br>There was mention that anyone that tried to harm the daughter of Innoruuk<br>would be killed without question.<br><br>She then began to lead us out into the woods speaking as she walked about<br>Cristianos Thex and the Royal house ... I let my mind wander then .. not<br>really paying attention to the Emissary's banter. There was something more<br>going on. I was sure of it. When she mentioned the Avatar of Hate I<br>listened a little closer. She spoke of recent events and how Innoruuk<br>demanded the life of his daughter. His own daughter? Fickle gods ... this<br>world is nothing but a game to them and we are their pawns to play with as<br>they like ... I know that now. And I guessed so would Lanys soon enough.<br><br>The Emissary came to a stop in front of the wizard platform ... I could<br>hear the humming caused from the magic of this ancient pad. I then moved<br>back out of the crowd and watched from afar.<br><br>The Emissary shouted out for a volunteer with loyalty to Innoruuk ... I<br>made no move ... I would have more loyalty to a frog but watched as others<br>thronged forward as if they were about to get some sort of precious prize.<br>The Emissary chose a very powerful master of the arcane though her name I<br>do not remember. She said it was through this woman that Lanys would be<br>summoned.<br><br>The hair on the back of my neck began to tingle I had heard of this<br>ceremony before but never had it been held is such a public place. The<br>Emissary asked for and received the hand of the chosen one. With a small<br>dagger she cut the arm, causing blood to flow onto the ground. The Chosen<br>made no sound as her life force drained from her. The Emissary waited a<br>moment and then healed the wound leaving a scar on the dark skin of the<br>other. As I watched the Emissary summoned an undead protector to her side<br>and then poured some blood red liquid onto the bones of her pet from a<br>silver bottle.<br><br>"With this, the crimson essence of life, the path has been placed."<br><br>The Emissary spoke in Teir`Dal ... I pondered if the few light dwellers<br>that had gathered could understand. My attention was drawn toward one<br>particular light dweller .. I small dwarf stood unafraid on the stairs of<br>the wizard gate. I had heard tales of this paladin, from Jusiel ... a<br>sister of sorts. His name was ... Grimm. I watched the flames of his sword<br>flickered and I hoped the brave one would not do anything foolish as he<br>watched the events unfold.<br><br>"With this, the chilled, hallow bones of death, the door is revealed."<br><br>My attention was drawn back to the ceremony as the pet lashed out at his<br>master, the Emissary. <br><br>"You now hold the key, the death is you door. Complete your task."<br><br>I pondered what that meant until the Chosen destroyed the pet with a mighty<br>cast of magic.<br><br>"Through the shadowed planes, she has been called."<br><br>There was a loud burst of magic on top of the wizard portal and out of the<br>smoke stepped the daughter of Innoruuk himself, Lanys T`Vyl. Her blood red<br>armor seemed to glow with unearthly magic.<br><br>I listened as the Emissary demanded she turn herself over to the protection<br>of The Dead and The Queen. Lanys refused and seemed very upset to have been<br>summoned from where ever she had been. The two spoke for some time ... and<br>again I must confess I did not listen all to clearly.<br><br>They spoke of another taking Lanys's place as Innoruuk's chosen, a child by<br>the name of Valizrae D`Tora. Lanys laughed and said she had the child and<br>was going to torture and scar her before binding her to this realm and then<br>killing her .. as some sort of warning to the gods.<br><br>Sometimes I have to wonder about the people of my birth .. these Teir`Dal<br>... so hungry for power.<br><br>The Emissary was not upset by the words spoken by Lanys ... said the<br>child's location within the ruins of Takish Hiz was known and the child<br>would be rescued before Lanys could harm her.<br><br>This seemed to upset Lanys and she turned to leave only to find herself<br>still bound to the forest by the blood on the ground. She screamed out her<br>frustration for the betrayal she felt. Just then with another show of power<br>Ashteth T`Dral self proclaimed Prophet of Innoruuk appeared.<br><br>I sighed ... I felt I was in middle of some kind of chess game ... and<br>wondered who would be king first.<br><br>Ashteth hand nothing new to offer Lanys and only seemed to upset her more<br>by being there. I knew then the Emissary would not get Lanys to come<br>peaceful ... and pondered if I should move further back for the battle that<br>would come.<br><br>Just then rain began to fall and I saw the shoulders of Lanys relax a<br>little as she turned and smiled at the Emissary. The rain had washed away<br>the blood on the ground, the bind that held Lanys was no more. With one<br>more warning of the war being her destiny then so be it, the daughter of<br>the god of Hate returned to where ever she had been summoned from.<br><br>I thought the show was over as the Emissary turned to leave. However, The<br>Prophet was not done and called the Emissary to his side. She approached<br>with caution but respect and bowed before him.<br><br>He asked her what she believed.<br><br>I chuckled ... glad he did not ask that question to me, afraid he would<br>strike me dead if I answered true to my heart.<br><br>The Emissary took a moment to answer and then told The Prophet that Lanys<br>was the daughter of Innoruuk and Naythox's methods to subdue her for a<br>sacrifice was disrespectful to one that had been revered by the Teir`Dal<br>for so long.<br><br>Sacrificed? I had to smile ... brought in for questioning had been what<br>they had tried to make her believe ... now the truth had been told.<br><br>The Prophet did not seem to be happy with her answer and I watched as he<br>placed hand on her forehead. I knew the spell he cast ... as an enchanter I<br>have used it many times on my foes. He was making her forget. I could sense<br>magic and pondered what lies he was filling the Emissary with now. <br><br>Another move had been made in the game of the gods I was sure. It was then<br>that I took my leave, afraid the dark one would work his magic on the<br>masses and make us forget what was known. <br><br>I hurried from the forest toward the commons .. I would buy the things I<br>needed in Freeport .. this forest was darker then usual. As I broke free of<br>the forest I was blinded for a moment by the light of the East Commons.<br>Before I regained my site strong arms grabbed me and lifted me into the<br>air. I smiled down at my beloved as my white hair fell down across his<br>beard. His image shimmered and his pale skin turned dark.<br><br>He held me in his embrace and for a moment I felt safe but the words of<br>Lanys came back to me ... there was a war coming ... the very soul of<br>Norrath knew that. I just had to ponder what God would get to say Checkmate<br>at the end of it?<br><br>Koori<br>Bristlebane Server<br>18th Level Enchantress

