<SPAN CLASS="pagesub">Real Men, Real Roleplayers, Loonies and Munchkins</SPAN><br>
<img src="/images/topback.jpg" valign="bottom" width=475 height=2><br>
<SPAN CLASS="credit">Author:</SPAN> 
<span class="credit2">See Below  (<a href="mailto:N/A" class="credit2">N/A</a>)</SPAN>&nbsp;&nbsp;  
<SPAN CLASS="credit">Organization:</SPAN> <a href="" class="credit2">N/A</a><br>

<SPAN CLASS="regtext">
<!-- Begin Content -->
<P>
EQ version by Rolli Polli of Rodcet Nife (aka Ed Macauley).  Based on the original work by Jeff Okamoto, Sandy Petersen, and lots of others.  <br> <br>The Real Man<br>The tough macho type who walks up to the sleeping dragon and orders it to leave before he gets hurt.<br> <br>The Real Roleplayer<br>The intelligent cunning guy who figures out the quest ten minutes after it comes into the game.<br> <br>The Loonie<br>The guy who will do anything for a cheap laugh, including casting four DOTs on himself and then run around screaming &#8220;help me.&#8221;<br> <br>The Munchkin<br>Need we say more?<br> <br>Character Relationships<br> <br>On real men:<br>Real Men think they're brothers in arms. <br>Real Roleplayers hide behind them. <br>Loonies harass them with stupid suggestions. <br>Munchkins say, &#8220;I'm a Real Man, too!&#8221;<br> <br>On Real Roleplayers:<br>Real Men protect them, on the off chance they may come up with something useful. <br>Real Roleplayers sigh with relief to know they're not alone, and then get their characters involved in love affairs and death feuds. <br>Loonies harass them with stupid suggestions. <br>Munchkins say, &#8220;I'm a Real Roleplayer, too!'' <br> <br>On Loonies:<br>Real Men ignore them. <br>Real Roleplayers sometimes harass them back by taking a stupid suggestion and making it work. <br>Loonies declare a pie fight at 20 paces . . . and cheat. <br>Munchkins try to imitate the jokes, and fall flat. <br> <br>On Munchkins:<br>Real Men attack them on sight. <br>Real Roleplayers trick them into being cannon fodder. <br>Loonies make reasonable-sounding suggestions that will get the Munchkin killed in an amusing way. <br>Munchkins ask, &#8220;What's a Munchkin?&#8221;<br> <br>Naming Convention:<br>Real Men keep their names short and sweet like Crush Dem or Hawk.<br>Real Roleplayers have elaborate fantasy names like Giovanni Stonecrusher.<br>Loonies make puns with their names like Rolli Polli or Wholly Molli.<br>Munchkins have names like Belgarion, Gandalf, Thor, Alley McBeal, Bigbootie, and Shiznat.<br> <br>Favorite Class:<br>Real Men play warriors, paladins, and rangers.<br>Real Roleplayers play clerics, enchanters, and shamans.<br>Loonies play gnome warriors or rogues.<br>Munchkins play druids and necromancers.<br> <br>Favorite Race:<br>Real Men play Barbarians, Trolls, Ogres and Humans.<br>Real Roleplayers play Humans, Elves, Erudites, and Iksar.<br>Loonies play Gnomes and Halflings.<br>Munchkins play whatever gives them the best stats.<br> <br>Role they play in a group:<br>Real Men prefer to be tanks or nukers.<br>Real Roleplayers like to be healers or support casters.<br>Loonies are comic relief.<br>Munchkins /shout, &#8220;I need a group!  C&#8217;mon guyz!  Who wants to group with me!&#8221;<br> <br>Favorite Type of Undead:<br>Real Men like ghouls.<br>Real Roleplayers like zombies.<br>Loonies like a troll wearing a white sheet.<br>Munchkins like whatever drops the most treasure.<br> <br>Favorite Type of Giant:<br>Real Men like hill giants.<br>Real Roleplayers like sand giants.<br>Loonies like the New York Giants.<br>Munchkins like whatever drops the most treasure.<br> <br>Favorite Type of Orc:<br>Real Men like Crushbone Orcs.<br>Real Roleplayers like Frost Orcs.<br>Loonies like Richard Nixon.<br>Munchkins don&#8217;t like orcs because they don&#8217;t have enough treasure.<br> <br>Favorite Creature to Fight (overall):<br>Real Men love to kill giants.<br>Real Roleplayers fight Froglok ghouls.<br>Loonies try to pickpocket the Priest of Discord.<br>Munchkins attack whatever YOU are fighting / whatever drops the most treasure.<br> <br>Favorite Zone in the Game (overall):<br>Real Men like South Karana<br>Real Roleplayers like the Ocean of Tears<br>Loonies like Rivervale<br>Munchkins like whatever has the most treasure.<br> <br>Favorite Spell:<br>Real Men like Chloroplast.<br>Real Roleplayers like Spirit of Wolf.<br>Loonies enjoy charming hill giants and then shrinking them.<br>Munchkins want control GM.<br> <br>How they ask for a Spirit of Wolf.<br>Real Men say, &#8220;Hi, could I get a sow?&#8221;<br>Real Roleplayers say, &#8220;Pardon me good Druid, but might I be imbued with the Spirit of Wolf?&#8221;<br>Loonies say, &#8220;Hey, you got a female pig?&#8221;<br>Munchkins say, &#8220;sow plz!  sow plz! I NEED SOW PLZ!&#8221;<br> <br>Combat Styles:<br>Real Men wade straight into a fight.<br>Real Roleplayers heal their comrades.<br>Loonies throw their sword at opponent then attack with their rusty dagger.<br>Munchkins wait until YOUR creature is halfway dead and nuke it, or they just kite.<br> <br>Favorite Combat Activity:<br>Real Men fight as many white and blue MOBs as they can at once.<br>Real Roleplayers gang up on one red MOB.<br>Loonies beg from the MOB while you kill it.<br>Munchkins camp, start trains, beg for heals and annoy everyone.<br> <br>Favorite Dungeon Activity:<br>Real Men like to clear out a dungeon room by room.<br>Real Roleplayers seek for quests.<br>Loonies forget that they are bound in the AOF room in Cazic Thule.<br>Munchkins camp, start trains, beg for heals and annoy everyone.<br> <br>Favorite Outdoor Activity:<br>Real Men find a camp of monsters and kill them.<br>Real Roleplayers like to track their prey.<br>Loonies fish and drink.<br>Munchkins camp, start trains, beg for heals and annoy everyone.<br> <br>Favorite Town Activity:<br>Real Men train at their guilds and get back to adventuring.<br>Real Roleplayers gather with their friends for a few drinks at the bar.<br>Loonies hold drunken scale of wolf footraces in Kelethin.<br>Munchkins camp, start trains, beg for heals and annoy everyone.<br> <br>Favorite GM-Event Activity:<br>Real Men beat back the hordes of monsters.<br>Real Roleplayers try to figure out the plot.<br>Loonies cast bind sight on Mayong Mistmoore and watch him kill everybody.<br>Munchkins camp, start trains, beg for heals and annoy everyone.<br> <br>Favorite Non-EQ activity:<br>Real Men hang out with their friends.<br>Real Roleplayers hang out with their friends.<br>Loonies hang out with their friends.<br>Munchkins Huh?<br> <br>Favorite Low-Level Dungeon:<br>Real Men like Crushbone.<br>Real Roleplayers enjoy Befallen.<br>Loonies like the Qeynos aqueducts.<br>Munchkins like Lower Guk.<br> <br>Favorite Mid-Level Dungeon:<br>Real Men hang out in Unrest.<br>Real Roleplayers like Cazic Thule.<br>Loonies like Rivervale.<br>Munchkins prefer the plane of fear.<br> <br>Favorite High-Level Dungeon:<br>Real Men kill things in Solusek Ro.<br>Real Roleplayers like Lower Guk.<br>Loonies like Rivervale.<br>Munchkins prefer the plane of hate.<br> <br>Favorite Ultra-High Level Area:<br>Real Men go to the planes.<br>Real Roleplayers go to the planes.<br>Loonies like Rivervale.<br>Munchkins don&#8217;t think the planes are enough of a challenge to solo.<br> <br>How they Warn about Trains:<br>Real Men shout, &#8220;Train to the zone, move it or lose it!&#8221;<br>Real Roleplayers shout, &#8220;Train, draw steel or die!&#8221;<br>Loonies shout, &#8220;De train boss!  De train!&#8221;<br>Munchkins don&#8217;t warn you.<br> <br>Auction Style:<br>Real Men auction, &#8220;Selling crafted BP, 1kpp obo&#8221;<br>Real Roleplayers auction, &#8220;I have a crafted breastplate for sale, pray do tell me with your offers.&#8221;<br>Loonies don&#8217;t have the attention span to auction.<br>Munchkins auction, &#8220;wts Crafted BP, FBSS, SSOY, Ro BP, YKWC, RMH or trade for Necro stuff.&#8221;<br> <br>How they Feel about Camping:<br>Real Men hate it but will help a friend get an item they&#8217;ve been after.<br>Real Roleplayers don&#8217;t camp.<br>Loonies don&#8217;t have the attention span to camp.<br>Munchkins say, &#8220;d00d!  I just camped the FBSS for 12 hours, now I&#8217;m gonna go pick up a GB, then I&#8217;m headed over to get the maid and butler fangs.&#8221;<br> <br>How they Feel about the &#8220;Play Nice&#8221; Policy:<br>Real Men don&#8217;t need it anyway.<br>Real Roleplayers are fine with it.<br>Loonies never interact with it in the first place.<br>Munchkins hate it because it limits their ability to play the game.<br> <br>Favorite Low Level Weapon:<br>Real Men use minotaur axes.<br>Real Roleplayers use a runed totem staff.<br>Loonies like rusty daggers.<br>Munchkins use Ghoulbane or Ykesha.<br> <br>Favorite Mid Level Weapon:<br>Real Men use a shiny brass halberd.<br>Real Roleplayers like the screaming mace.<br>Loonies like rusty daggers.<br>Munchkins use an electrum bladed wakazashi.<br> <br>Favorite High Level Weapon:<br>Real Men like Ykesha.<br>Real Roleplayers want a Ghoulbane.<br>Loonies like rusty daggers.<br>Munchkins haven&#8217;t found anything good yet.<br> <br>Favorite Ultra-High Level Weapon:<br>Real Men like the Electrum Bladed Wakazashi.<br>Real Roleplayers want a Firey Avenger.<br>Loonies use rusty daggers.<br>Munchkins want a BFG.<br> <br>How they Deal with Death:<br>Real Men suck it up and keep playing.<br>Real Roleplayers /cry over soandso&#8217;s corpse.<br>Loonies keep score based on &#8220;The Art of Dying.&#8221;<br>Munchkins say, &#8220;Dude, no worries, I&#8217;ve got a LVL 50 cleric.&#8221;<br> <br>Favorite Way of Getting Information about a quest:<br>Real Men ask their Real Roleplayer friends.<br>Real Roleplayers figure it out the hard way.<br>Loonies don&#8217;t do quests because their attention span is too short.<br>Munchkins look it up on the Internet.<br> <br>Favorite Food to take on Expeditions:<br>Real Men forage for their food.<br>Real Roleplayers buy rations.<br>Loonies bring along edible goo.<br>Munchkins say, &#8220;d00d, can I have some water?&#8221;<br> <br>Favorite Kind of Elf: <br>Real Men like the Pinis' elves.<br>Real Roleplayers like Tolkien's elves.<br>Loonies like Santa's elves.<br>Munchkins like Storm Giants with pointed ears.<br> <br>Favorite Kind of Dwarf: <br>Real Men like AD&D Dwarves.<br>Real Roleplayers like Tolkien's Dwarves.<br>Loonies like the Seven Dwarves.<br>Munchkins like Earth Elementals with beards.<br> <br>Favorite Fantasy Author<br>Real Men read Glen Cook.<br>Real Roleplayers read J.R.R. Tolkien.<br>Loonies read Robert Asprin.<br>Munchkins read E. Gary Gygax.<br> <br>Favorite Music:<br>Real Men listen to Led Zeppelin.<br>Real Roleplayers listen to 14th-century madrigals.<br>Loonies listen to Weird Al Yankovic.<br>Munchkins listen to rap.<br> <br>The quote that best describes their destiny in life:<br>Real Men, &#8220;Look out Mr. President!  He&#8217;s got a gun!&#8221;<br>Real Roleplayers, &#8220;I&#8217;d like to thank the academy&#8230;&#8221;<br>Loonies, &#8220;Thanks, you&#8217;ve been a great audience.&#8221;<br>Munchkins, &#8220;Would you like fries with that?&#8221;

