<SPAN CLASS="pagesub">General Alchemy Info for Buyers/Makers of Potions</SPAN><br>
<img src="/images/topback.jpg" valign="bottom" width=475 height=2><br>
<SPAN CLASS="credit">Author:</SPAN> 
<span class="credit2">Mebe Spiritbringer   (<a href="mailto:N/A" class="credit2">N/A</a>)</SPAN>&nbsp;&nbsp;  
<SPAN CLASS="credit">Organization:</SPAN> <a href="" class="credit2">Halo of Fire</a><br>

<SPAN CLASS="regtext">
<!-- Begin Content -->
<P>
Greetings!<br><br>For those who do not know, as of this writing (6/21/2000), I am a level 52<br>Shaman with a 134 Alchemy skill. Just so you know my credentials ;)<br><br>I recently started selling gate potions. While this increased quite a bit<br>the number of questions I field everyday, I have always been asked things<br>about Alchemy. Also, on a regular basis, I have had to correct people with<br>misconceptions about Alchemy and the potions Alchemists can make.<br><br>This document is an attempt to address some of these in a public forum, sort<br>of a pre-emptive strike as it were.<br><br>*All player made alchemy potions have a CASTING TIME<br><br>**This means that all player made alchemy potions can be interrupted, just<br>like if you were casting a spell.<br><br>***However, the potion is not used up if interrupted, so you can try again.<br><br>*No Alchemy potions are stackable in Inventory<br><br>*Each potion is ONE dose, meaning that if it is successfully used, it goes<br>away. Just like a beer, you drink the beer, the beer goes away.<br><br>*Any race/class can use any Alchemy potion<br><br>*All potions that raise your Stats (STR, DEX, etc.) STACK with player cast<br>buffs. I call these STAT potions.<br><br>**All STAT potions have side effects, positive and negative. For example:<br>Greater Potion of Purity is +25 STR, +15 DEX and MINUS 20 STAmina (about<br>45hp for a level 50 shaman if remember right) However, if you are the dmg<br>dealer, and not the dmg taker, this is a great buff for warriors and melee<br>types with Proccing weapons. BTW, there are other STR potions with different<br>side effects.<br><br>**There are two types of potions. There are auras and then there are the<br>other physical stat potions. The auras are the potions with resists.<br><br>***Not all Aura potions will stack with the other potions. Of the ones that<br>can, you can only stack one aura potion with one physical stat potion. NOTE:<br>Purity and Power do NOT stack<br><br>*Potions that increase a STAT and/or resistance put up a Buff Icon. If your<br>screen has 15 buff Icons up already, it will not work. You will be given the<br>"This spell did not take hold" message and your potion will be GONE.<br><br>*Invis VS Undead Potion (IVU) works exactly like the player cast spell. So,<br>the duration is random. Also, if a MOB would see through an IVU spell cast<br>by a player, it will also see through the IVU potion. They are the same<br>effect.<br><br>*SoW Potions work in OUTDOOR zones only. If Shaman/Druid can CAST SoW in a<br>zone, then you can drink the potion in that zone. You can however drink the<br>potion while in an OUTDOOR zone and then go into an indoor zone and you will<br>still have SoW speed. Again, works just like the player cast SoW. Have been<br>told by customers that they last a long time tho, longer than a SoW buff<br>from a player.<br><br>*Shrink Potions currently work in DUNGEONS only (Fear and Hate zones are not<br>considered dungeons, although Sky is). Again, if a Shaman can cast the<br>Shrink spell in the zone, then you can use the potion too. It lasts as long<br>you stay in the zone. However, it will go away when you camp, sometimes when<br>you go LD, and if you change your form after drinking the potion (IOW, if<br>you drink shrink potion, then cast wolf form, shrink will go away. If you<br>want to be a teeny tiny wolf, go wolf form first, THEN drink potion) One<br>note on this, Verant has said that they will be making the potion work in<br>all zones "soon", whenever that is.<br><br>*Damage Shield potions are DRINKER dependant. (Level/4)+1 truncated (not<br>exact, but very close). So, no, you can't buy them for your level 4<br>character for twinking, unless you only want a 2 point damage shld. A level<br>48 player gets a 13 point Dmg Shld. Lasts 8 to 9 minutes and STACKS with ALL<br>player cast Damage shields.<br><br>*Potion of Frost goes to Everfrost. Have been told it drops you in the 3<br>Igloo area in Everfrost, near BB. If you can confirm, please do so :)<br><br>*Potion of Swamp goes to Innothule Swamp. You land in the Southern Hand that<br>sticks out of the swamp, where the Shadowmen are. Shadowmen pose me no<br>problems, but probably depends on your class/level. I wouldn't use Swamp<br>potion if you were level 20, that's for sure. The Feerrott zone is West of<br>the Hand<br><br>*The Lizard Blood Potion is NOT made by alchemists, it is dropped by a MoB.<br><br>*Alchemy made gate potions (Frost and Swamp) have about a 25 second casting<br>time (according to a customer report). Obviously not a get-away-quick<br>potion. It is a transportation potion. To help Tanks stuck in fear, or deep<br>inside a dungeon, when no porters are available, or even as a way to get to<br>Everfrost more quickly than porting to NK. I'm sure you can come up with<br>many other situations where it would be handy (Can we say Kunark? I knew you<br>could, hehe).<br><br>*The cost to a shaman to make a Potion is NOT the cost of the herbs that<br>make it. For example, using nice round fictional numbers that do not relate<br>to any potion in particular: Potion of Uberness requires Herb X and Herb Y.<br>Herb X costs 15pp and Herb Y costs 5pp. This means that the total cost per<br>ATTEMPT to make the potion is 20pp. If the Alchemists is 100% successful<br>(yea, right, heh) then it does indeed cost 20pp to make. BUT, if the success<br>rate is 75% instead, it actually costs the alchemist 26.7pp per success. If<br>50%, would cost 40pp per success. If 25%, would cost 80pp per success. That<br>is the cost to the alchemist to make the potion. From there, it is up to the<br>individual Alchemist to decide on a fair profit margin for himself and the<br>customer. But please do not confuse cost per attempt with cost per success.<br>I am constantly running into people who have gone on a website somewhere,<br>jotted down herb component prices, and now think they know how much it costs<br>to make the potion and try to argue with me about my prices.<br><br>*Alchemy skill is Level Capped and is a Shaman Only Skill. (Level-24)*5 For<br>example, a level 50 Shaman would have a cap of 130: (50-24)*5=130 This means<br>you must be at least at level 25 before being able to do any alchemy. Would<br>not suggest trying to make gate potions until skill of 130, although some<br>have started at 120 on other servers. Even if you start at 120 skill, you<br>have to be level 48 to be able to get a skill that high. So, no, you can't<br>create a mule shaman to make gate potions for you unless you are willing to<br>Powerlevel the Shaman to level 48-50 and are willing to spend lots of plat,<br>even with the price redux in herbs, will still take LOTS of plat to raise<br>your skill high enough after you get level 48.<br><br>I would like to thank the people of Bristlebane who frequent The Inn of<br>Bristlebane (<a href="http://www.draedon.com/cgi-bin/inn.pl">http://www.draedon.com/cgi-bin/inn.pl</a>) who helped with various<br>info and questions.<br><br>--Mebe Spiritbringer of Bristlebane (Halo of Fire)

<!-- End Content -->
