<SPAN CLASS="pagesub">The Skill of Pick Pocket: Pros & Cons</SPAN><br>
<img src="/images/topback.jpg" valign="bottom" width=475 height=2><br>
<SPAN CLASS="credit">Author:</SPAN> 
<span class="credit2">Kambic  (<a href="mailto:N/A" class="credit2">N/A</a>)</SPAN>&nbsp;&nbsp;  
<SPAN CLASS="credit">Organization:</SPAN> <a href="http://pub2.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse" class="credit2">The Safe House</a><br>

<SPAN CLASS="regtext">
<!-- Begin Content -->
<P>
I play a Rogue, which happens to be the only class that gets the skill "Pick Pocket." This means that if the player base were equally divided, at most less then 8% of the player base (over level 7) would have ever even used this skill, let alone understands it. Rogues are one of the least played classes, which makes this percentage even smaller. It is my goal to share with you the workings of Pick Pocket.<br><br>Pick Pocket has been an issue nearly since release, and is often the deciding factor on a Rogue getting a group. Despite good, fast damage, unrivaled scouting and excellent corpse recovery, the Rogue class is still looked down upon simply because of this skill. Let me explain a few things about it.<br><br>Rogues acquire "Pick Pocket" at Level 7. It has a 10 second recycle time. First and foremost, nothing can be Pick Pocketed that is marked MAGIC or any items that are equipped; only humanoid creatures can be Pick Pocketed (i.e. no undead or animals). On top of that, no MOBs level 45+ can be Pick Pocketed whatsoever. Also, the Rogue has no control over what is taken items or coins. Even though items can be pick pocketed, it is a rare thing in the life of the Rogue. The majority of the time, coins will be stolen. Even then, it's not guaranteed that very much will be taken. At level 15, it is very rare for me to Pick Pocket Gold, Silver is almost common, but the majority of what I steal is Copper. I have never stolen Platinum. The deciding factor on how much is stolen (and how much can be stolen) is ultimately based on the MOB's loot pool. Although there was previously a bug that allowed a Rogue to endlessly steal small amounts of Copper, this has been corrected and everything stolen is now taken from the loot pool. So if the loot is considerably lower then normal, there has probably been a lot of Pick Pocketing going on (or an avid fan of the skill "Beg" hehe); you can also tell when a Rogue steal because many (mind you, not all) MOB's will yell, "Stop Thief! <Rogue's name>"<br><br>As unfriendly as this skill sounds it can be useful to others besides the Rogue. Although Rogues are a pure melee class, we don't get the skill "Taunt." Many of us would like it, to have even better personal crowd control (in addition to Evade). As Backstab has a taunt factor built into it, so does Pick Pocket. It is possible to taunt a MOB off someone with Pick Pocket.<br><br>One of the main reason we like to Pick Pocket is simply to keep this skill maxed out. Around level 20+, Pick Pocketing becomes more of a hindrance then a help to a Rogue. The constant loot of small change quickly adds to his weight, thus making the coins virtually useless.<br><br>I, and the majority of the Rogues I know, ask before Pick Pocketing in a group. If you are a Rogue reading this, or an aspiring one, I encourage you to do the same. I hope that we can make this skill more understood and less rejected. <br><br>The Safehouse (*THE* Rogue message forum) has many excellent FAQ's and guides about the Rogue class. One of them happens to be about Pick Pocket. If you are interested to know more, I'd advise you to go to this link to learn more: <a href="http://pub2.ezboard.com/fthesafehouselibraryreadonly.showMessage?topicID=20.topic">Tome of Mastery: Picking Pockets</a>.<br><br>Kambic the Rogue<br>Rallos Zek       <br>Of the Safehouse

<!-- End Content -->
