<SPAN CLASS="pagesub">The Naming Policy</SPAN><br>
<img src="/images/topback.jpg" valign="bottom" width=475 height=2><br>
<SPAN CLASS="credit">Author:</SPAN> 
<span class="credit2">Ulalume  (<a href="mailto:N/A" class="credit2">N/A</a>)</SPAN>&nbsp;&nbsp;  
<SPAN CLASS="credit">Organization:</SPAN> <a href="" class="credit2">N/A</a><br>

<SPAN CLASS="regtext">
<!-- Begin Content -->
<P>
On this topic, I definitely know what I'm talking about. I used to work at AOL's TOS (Terms of Service) department. Some of you might be familiar with them... My primary job was to scan the thousands of room names and screen names and get rid of the ones that were offensive in AOL's sole discretion. Room names like DADEESPANKZLILGRL and EYEKUM4UNOW were verboten and therefore removed from the public eye. It was a never-ceasing job. For 8 hours a day I scanned lists over and over and over, searching the creative and obscure spellings for vulgarity, illegal activity, and unacceptable behavior. Yes, I was the Thought Police. ;) After a few weeks of practice, I could scan a list of a couple of hundred names in a few seconds and pick out the ones that were vulgar. It became reflex. <br><br>One of the more insidious consequences of this work was the eventual ability to spot hidden vulgarity in license plates, internet names, etc. And especially EQ character names, even when the player behind the name hadn&#8217;t intended it. For instance, I came across the seemingly-innocent name Canilea on one of the servers. I started laughing and sent a tell to the unfortunate young lady, letting her know that I thought her character name was funny. When she questioned me about it, having no idea what I meant, I carefully explained to her that the name said &#8220;Can I lay ya?&#8221; She reacted rather violently and pretty much called me a pervert. Rather than explain why I couldn&#8217;t HELP but see something off-color in her name, I just let her think I was a random psycho and vowed not to do that again. Instead, I&#8217;ll merely stick with /petitioning those names that I find that should be removed from the game. <br><br>I rather enjoy seeing all those unique fantasy names, and I admit that names like Dudeone, Raistlin, Gandalf, or Anikan Skiwolker (yes, the name exists on one of the servers) really bother me and for just a few minutes sort of suck some of the fun out of the game. Mind you, I&#8217;m not a die-hard in-game roleplayer, but names like that just bug me. In Greater Faydark, which seems to collect all the psychos of Norrath in one neat little package, I came across the name Filatio. For those of you who don&#8217;t know why that bothered me, I humbly suggest that you look up the word fellatio in a good dictionary. Filatio happens to be a homonym of it. I can&#8217;t imagine that the person who created that name didn&#8217;t know what they were doing. It&#8217;s just too convenient. But then, I was trained to be cynical about that sort of thing. Regardless, homonyms of vulgar words are, according to Verant&#8217;s policy, not allowed. I petitioned the name THREE times on separate days. For some reason, the guides and GM&#8217;s wouldn&#8217;t get rid of this obviously illegal and irritating name. I have no idea if it&#8217;s still in the game or not, but it SHOULD have been removed. Immediately. <br><br>The point? The point is that no matter what Abashi says on the subject, I absolutely, willfully REFUSE TO BELIEVE that there are real, live human beings who check the character names as they are created. If so, there wouldn&#8217;t be all those names like Buttmuncher, Biteme, and Darthmaul. If there are actually people screening those names, I humbly suggest that they be trained a little better. Or at the least, Verant should change their policy and hire specific individuals whose sole job it is to monitor game content instead of letting every on-duty guide and GM serve as a bulwark for inappropriate names. Hire someone with a decent vocabulary who can recognize homonyms and obscure references. And for pity&#8217;s sake, take out the Star Wars names&#8230; They&#8217;re gonna get a WHOLE GAME ALL TO THEMSELVES soon. And man, I just can&#8217;t wait to get rid of &#8216;em. <br><br>Ulalume (That&#8217;s from a Poe poem, y&#8217;all&#8212;guilty as charged) <br>Ranger, The Tribunal 

