<P>
Well, now I feel the perfect fool.  There I was thinking nobody who read my last article felt it hard-hitting or controversial enough to comment on it.  It was a supreme downer to find my mailbox empty week after week, but I figured that lent me time to work on my fictional story (which is coming along nicely, by the way).  Then, to my shock and horror, I discovered that the web mail service I use had, once again and without telling anyone, changed the interface so that it no longer automatically downloaded mail from external accounts.  Well, isn't that just precious?<P>The next thing I know, I'm looking at page after page of e-mail from people who obviously care about me a great deal.  They took the time to let me know how I too can make an extra ten thousand dollars a month just from working out of my home!<P>Then came the reader response mail - droves of them.  It took me a solid three-and-a-half-hours of reading to get through them all.  I was so overjoyed, I couldn't help but grab one of my co-workers and throttle him until his tongue hung out and his eyes rattled in his skull.  (Simmer down, Dave - I know you have good medical coverage.)<P>After my mistaken assumption, I can't put to words how grateful I am to you all for writing in.  I received mail of support saying "right on," and "I couldn't have said it better myself," by the truckloads.  Every single one brought a smile to my face, and my thanks goes out to each of you, bar none.  Other letters I received told stories of times they had been killed by a player-killer who actually <I>did</I> roleplay the scene out.  All I can say is that your stories were entertaining, inspiring, and I envy each and every one of you with a seething, unending jealousy!  I even received a tempting offer by a concerned player named "Yibno" to kill me in a fully roleplayed scene.  It's a shame I stopped playing on Rallos Zek...<P>As per my usual habits, I'm here now to post and respond to a number of thought-provoking letters.  As with the many kudos I received, the intelligent, well-thought-out e-mails were bountiful to the nines.  I sincerely wish I could post each of them here, or even drop a personal note to all the people who took the time to write in their thoughts and contentions.  Sadly, due to sheer volume, I'm only able to post a handful of them here.  And though it pains me, it's a personal policy for me not to reply via e-mail, as that would make me start thinking about all those other e-mails that were deserving of a response.  Soon, I'm writing nothing but e-mails and not editorials, and that's not the pic-a-nic basket I'm looking to swallow, Boo-Boo.<P>I'll start with the one and only mindless letter I received.  I promised in the article that anyone who started flaming me as anti-PK was going to be made to look all the more hose-brained in the reader responses.  As I am a man of my word, here is the following mail...<P>----------<P><FONT COLOR="0000AA">So I am a stupid player-killer huh...  I pk all the time for fun.<BR>Reguardless if I know the player or not. <BR>The reason:  It is fun. <BR><P></FONT>I'm gratified beyond words.<FONT COLOR="0000AA"><P>In a savage environment like the mid-evil times there were knights of valor <BR>which killed rogue assasins all the time.  Just as there are some Everquest <BR>paladins who feel it is there job as well.  During mid evil times some <BR>Rogues would kill only for money.  Some even rape and pillaged. Now EQ is <BR>set in a mid evil like time.  There wasn't always honor back then.  And if <BR>you are a cleric dressed in your richly churchly clothes and I see you are <BR>hurt.  Yes I would lift my blade to kill you. <BR><P></FONT>Actually, in <I>medieval</I> times, people like that were publicly executed in a rousing, typically gruesome event as an example of what happened to such criminals.  You get away with that role in EverQuest because somehow the local governments don't object to their citizenry being butchered outside their guarded borders.  And it may come as a surprise to you that death in the real world is <I>permanent</I> - even in medieval times.  You're comparing apples to oranges in your justification, bud... never a good idea.<FONT COLOR="0000AA"><P>If I kill all the time because I play my character as a rogue with a metal <BR>problem then DEAL with it. <BR>If you can't and you call my situation inwhich I killed you cheap THEN YES <BR>THERE IS ONLY ONE GOOD ANSWER I CAN GIVE YOU. <BR><P>GO TO THE BLUE SERVERS. <P></FONT>At this point, I laughed out loud.  And here I thought I'd seen the last of the old tired "raving lunatic who runs around killing everyone" rationale for player killing.<P>If your character is stark-raving mad, so be it.  All I ask is that you put some effort into it and actually (gasp) <I>do something</I> that lets people know that's what you are.  If you haven't tried it, I recommend doing so - you might like it.<FONT COLOR="0000AA"><P>Reason why:  You can not change ppl.  They will have to want to change.  All <BR>your letter did was fire up others and I think you are enjoying the <BR>attention and I rarely give that so feel lucky. <BR><P></FONT>Exsqueeze me?  When did I say I wanted to change people's play habits?  If I had to summarize the editorial it would be to say that player-killers should expect certain social consequences to their actions.  How is that changing what they do?<P>I take that back.  There is one thing I would change about people, and that would be for them to actually read an article or message board posting before voicing an ill-informed opinion.  <FONT COLOR="0000AA"><P>-Sincerely (Davidn) <---- This is the lowest pk character that is insane. <BR>But my highest characters (43, 50, and 50) which will remain anon feel some <BR>of your pain and advise you that as Verant said nothing and no material <BR>should mean that much in the game that you are afraid to loose it.<BR></FONT><P>----------<P>Congratulations, Sincerely (Davidn).  You just won the cranial enema of honor.  Next time I suggest you think "topical" before you put another thought to the written word.<P>I'll say it again: I - am - not - anti - PK.  To anyone not in favor of open player-versus-player combat, I strongly recommend bugging out of Rallos Zek.  The fact is, I'm not.  I never said I was.  End of discussion.  If that's not good enough for you, sir, then it is you who must "deal with it."<P>The next letter is from another player-killer who tends to express his views in a more clear and concise manner...<P>----------<P><FONT COLOR="0000AA">Yes yes, most of your points are correct, im glad we somewhat understand<BR>each other. I knew about every consequence and reprecusion of my actions<BR>before i started pking, and accepted them.<BR><P>I assume one of these was directed at me "Filthey McNastey"...<BR><P>"I have reformed, i dont pk anymore, blah blah blah i ask your<BR>forgiveness"<P></FONT>The incident I cited in the article was so long ago, I don't recall the name of the character.  I doubt it was you that I saw, but it's not mathematically impossible on a purely cosmic scale.<FONT COLOR="0000AA"><P>I NEVER asked anyone's forgiveness, i DID, however, get murdered<BR>repeatedly, and over the course of 2 months taking each one with no<BR>retaliation. After which i asked the ppl if they were satisfied, and<BR>when they told me yes, i said "then please, get over it".<BR><P>Now, this is not an unreasonable request, as most of the people that<BR>killed me i NEVER touched before. And they refused to leave me alone<BR>citing all this crap about how i sadistically castrated one of their<BR>guildmates or something...<BR><P></FONT>The request <I>is</I> unreasonable.  If I were one of your absent victims, I wouldn't care how many others killed you, or how many times they killed you, or how they weren't even victims if yours.  I wouldn't care that you profess not to PK anymore.  All I would care about is remuneration one way or another, be it that I kill you and retrieve my item and money or you give it back to me voluntarily.  Either way is fine by me, but certainly not the alleged acceptance of a handful of people I don't know whom you somehow see as speaking for me.<P>I agree, what happened to you was unfair - as much or more so than your actions might have merited.  But it doesn't settle matters, nor does it make them equal.  Not by a long shot.  I'm still out my property, and I will still be sorely angry over it, and I will despise you until the end of my days... erm, or I <I>would</I> if I were a victim, that is.<P>That is the reality of player killing, and that is the consequence.<FONT COLOR="0000AA"><P>[...]Anyway, just so we understand each other, i feel that you are one of the<BR>smarter people on rallos, but i dont agree with one aspect of your<BR>attitude towards pks. The part about how all people should deplore that<BR>behavior and how it is an affront to all the senses of everyone. And the<BR>part about how they tend to whine when they get ganged up on.<BR><P></FONT>I never said people should deplore that behavior.  I said that player-killers should expect it when they do.  I said it is an affront to most people's sense of honor and justice.  I don't see how you can equate "most" with "everyone."  Try again.<FONT COLOR="0000AA"><P>Seriously, nobody EVER whines about be ganged up on UNLESS they have hadNO time to prepare. YOU CANNOT say that uve heard whining about gang upswhen someone has been attacked for the first time. Its only AFTER theyare killed and you attack them at/near their corpse.<P></FONT>Do <I>not</I> presume to declare that I cannot say such a thing.  I do say it and I will continue to say it so long as it is the truth.  If you have encountered contrary behavior, fine, but I will not tolerate being labeled a liar, sir, by you or anyone else.<FONT COLOR="0000AA"><P>Just thought id share my views with you...<BR>No, i am not beaten by my parents<BR>No, i am not molested<BR>No, no tragic childhood of any kind<BR>No, i dont eat Belgian children<BR>Yes, i do it to have fun<BR>Yes, i do it for personal gain<BR>Yes, I have a good amount of friends, some of which DO play comp games,<BR>some of which don't<BR>I lift weights, i play Bball<BR>Thats me...<BR><P></FONT>I'm glad to hear it.<FONT COLOR="0000AA"><P>Sadly, this is not the vision i have of most EQ players, the ones that<BR>dont let things go, the ones that think pking is so deplorable. My<BR>vision of those ppl are ones that are somehow and in either a big or<BR>small way ostricized by society. Which psychologically explains why they<BR>do so much to "fit in" in EQ. I may be way off base here, i can admit<BR>that. But thats just what my psychology classes taught me, and the<BR>thoughts travel with each other logically.<BR><P></FONT>All I can say is, don't take everything you're told in psychology class as gospel.  It's not an exact science by any definition of the term, and I can guarantee that making general assumptions based on its principles will burn you.<FONT COLOR="0000AA"><P>Lastly, id like to know who you are on the server. Pardon me if umentioned it somewhere and i just didnt catch it.<P>Matt Sabo</FONT><P>----------<P>Sorry, Matt - no can do.  The last time I gave out one of my character names, I never heard the end of it.  Besides, I'm on a sabbatical of sorts from Rallos Zek.  We'll have to see if I ever return.<P>Next up is a segment from a letter sent to me by a pleasantly articulate reader.  For the sake of brevity, I'll quote the portion of the letter I'll be addressing...<P>----------<P><FONT COLOR="0000AA">[...]  What bothers me the most is,  <BR>is that there is no Pker  that has respect for the fellow player.  Believe me,<BR>in the right role-playing circumstances,  Dueling/Player Killing can be fun!<BR> A good fight is what I'm looking for!  That's what I thought Rallos Zek was<BR>supposed to be about!  Aye, I have yet to find anyone like that on Rallos and<BR>I don't want to imagine what it must be like on the PvP team servers.    I<BR>have thought a lot about the issue of Coin-loot only?  Will this make a<BR>difference?  Will my pride be any less hurt?   My pride probably won't, but<BR>my anger might be subsided a bit.  Most of the anger/resentment I feel<BR>towards a pker is that the only reason they killed me was for my item that I<BR>had worked to get or a precious gift from a friend.  [...]<P>Sincerely,<BR>BuffyAng Whitemajestic</FONT><P>----------<P>What you say about there being no player-killers who respect their fellow player isn't entirely true, though I agree that at times it can certainly seem like it.<P>It's the coin-only issue you bring up that caught my attention.  One thing you must keep in mind when considering the prospect of coin-only looting is that, by default, it comes with a price.  Part of the reason player combat is such an adrenaline rush is the fact that you're putting so much more on the line than life and limb and the time it takes to recover your corpse.  In the face of defeat, you stand to lose the very Shining Breastplate of Misshapen Denting that you so depend on to gain an advantage in the fight.  Without that risk, how much of the excitement is lost?  Will it be as much of a "good fight," as you're looking for?<P>The truth is, nobody's qualified to make that determination for anybody but themselves.  Personally, I don't think I would care to play on Rallos Zek if it's ever switched over, but I can see how it would be the proverbial Holy Grail for others.  You, on the other hand, may feel differently.<P>I'll tell you what.  Head on over to Tallon Zek and try it out.  See what you think.  If you like it, then great!  I say go with it!  If not, at least you gave it a shot.  <P>Moving on, here's someone who lives by their definition of roleplaying in the same way most people live (and die) by the sword...<P>----------<P><FONT COLOR="0000AA">The roleplay non roleplay topic is played to death...<P></FONT>I agree, and it will continue to be played to death until a happy medium is found.<FONT COLOR="0000AA"><P>What happens if your intent is to kill someone, and you stop to type out "Have at thee foul elf for the power of innoruk" well to put it mildy from another game "Kal Ort Por" If I am an ogre, or a DE, or a Troll, and I kill you I may or may not be roleplaying, to roleplay does not mean that I HAVE to talk to you. Seriously being a DE under the guidelines layed out, they are killed by nearly everyone...Do you expect that all DE's will be so kind enough as to tell you just exactly why he is about to kill you,or attempt to? <P></FONT>Oh, I dunno.  It always seemed to work for James Bond movies...<FONT COLOR="0000AA"><P>No he is not, and I would not consider having a social button to spam as you attack "ALL BUT DARK ELVES SHALL LIVE MY WRATH" asroleplaying, its just spam again. If you kill or if you do not kill isyour choice, but be warned, if someone is a DE out for phat lewt or not,if they kill you, don't complain its just a quake mentality, they areplaying a race which is expected to be killed and expected to be killed.A few choice word's during the attack is not needed or warrented due tothe fact that most people who are attacked will not fight, they will rununless they feel that they cannot possibly die.<P>Osiris TheMercs.org</FONT><P>----------<P>I have news for you, Osiris: They'll run anyway.<P>But your point is well taken.  Shouting insults at your opponent as you hack them to pieces isn't roleplaying in and of itself.  It may state your character as a devout member of his/her own race, but it isn't roleplaying.  Admittedly, it may fit your character's predefined persona to loom up, kill the victim, loot the corpse and vanish without a trace.  That's plenty fine as long as you realize that doing so is also the hallmark of a powergaming PK out for his next batch of "phat loot," and more often than not that is exactly how you will be perceived.  I can't change that, and quite honestly I don't see why it <I>should</I> be changed.<P>If that doesn't sit well with you, be imaginative in your approach.  Be creative in your actions, and more importantly in your <I>reactions</I>.  You'll have the distinction of playing your role better, I promise you that.  If nothing else, you can't be faulted for trying - it's failing to try that people should be faulted for, but never seem to be.<P>Here's someone who feels similarly with your sentiments...<P>----------<P><FONT COLOR="0000AA">do you play many roleplaying games besides eq? well if you fo thenroleplaying is  how you make a character...not how YOU think peopleshouold play them.    So what if someone wants their character to hate DE or Trolls, thatswhat roleplaying really is bud making your char how you see fit theyshould be played ... not by some gay idies of "i slay you in the name oftunare" when killing orcs thats bs,,,,, if you want to get into classspecific roleplaying then a shadow knight would kill anyone he sees andsame with trolls and ogres</FONT><P>----------<P>I do play other roleplaying games besides EverQuest.  Other multiplayer titles include Ultima Online, Asheron's Call, Baldur's Gate and Diablo as well as a dabbling in several MUDs and free-form chat rooms online.  I have played and game-mastered several pencil and paper roleplaying games, including Dungeon's and Dragons (Advanced and Basic), Gamma World, Star Frontiers, Mech Warrior, Star Wars and numerous other games my friends and I made up from scratch.  I have created characters with their own ambitions and drives that are not necessarily my own, both good and evil, male and female, mutant, alien and human alike.  Since the days of elementary school, I have led characters from humble beginnings to powerful and sometimes fearsome figures in the annals of countless worlds, at once playing the gallant hero who saves the day and the sinister villain who conquers with an iron fist.  I am now twenty-eight years old, and I still have not tired of exploring new worlds with my imaginary friends and their individual traits and faults in which I indulge myself.  Norrath is but one, single world among a thousand others I have visited through the eyes of my characters.<P>Don't preach to me what roleplaying is.  Judging by your letter, it's my bet I was roleplaying characters before you were on solid foods.<P>The following is an excerpt from a very long-winded, angry individual.  I love it when I touch a nerve... <P>----------<P><FONT COLOR="0000AA">[...]  "I don't care if it's in the game context or not, expect to be labeled a bad<BR>person"<P>You know, that's a VERY interesting statement, coming from someone who<BR>complains that PKs aren't roleplaying. If even killing other people within<BR>the context of the game is deplorable... then, what *isn't*?<BR><P></FONT>When did I say player-killers never roleplay?  That would be untrue.  I said I've never had a player-killer roleplay while they killed <I>me</I>.  That's factual.<FONT COLOR="0000AA"><P>Do you actually expect me to ask people if I can attack them, first? <P></FONT>Not if you don't want to.  You're free to play like a koala bear, for all the interest I have.  Just be aware of the consequences, and don't be an ass when they come back to bite you in yours.<FONT COLOR="0000AA"><P>Do you actually expect that I'm going to issue a duel-challenge to everyone <BR>I feel like killing? <P></FONT>*shrug*  If you like. In most cases it would be rather pointless to do so on the Rallos Zek server, but I won't complain if you do.<FONT COLOR="0000AA"><P>Seriously... what the heck is a Neutral Evil Dark Elf  Supposed to do, in<BR>order to gain the "Shadoe Seal Of Approval: Acceptable PK" award????<P></FONT>Nothing.  There's no such thing.  But I am gratified that you place so much stock into my opinion about your play style.<FONT COLOR="0000AA"><P>I think that, if you were to take the time to ask RZ players, you'd see that<BR>most of them have no objections to being attacked by someone of an obviously<BR>hostile race. Most people would tell you that the biggest issues on the<BR>server are the loot disparity between melee classes & casters, various<BR>camping exploits (zone, corpse, & bind-point), pet exploits, no ability to<BR>use Fear or Charm in PvP fights, twinking, & EBay farmers.<BR><P></FONT>Those are all valid concerns about EverQuest, but it doesn't negate the fact that I think your original assumption about Rallos Zek players is false.  <P>Even so, I never professed to speak for the majority of the playership.  In fact, as a roleplayer I'm vastly outnumbered when it comes to statistics.  This is my column, and these are my opinions and my thoughts, and I'll still say them even if 99% of my fellow players violently disagree.  To do otherwise would go against the point of having your own column.<FONT COLOR="0000AA"><P>cordially,<BR>Aumvaar Flaye<BR>Ambassador of The Horde</FONT><P>----------<P>(I love how he had the audacity to use the word "cordially.")<P>Let's switch gears for a while, and explore the the kinder, gentler side of Rallos Zek...<P>----------<P><FONT COLOR="0000AA">Dang, your article about PK, its all true.  Preach on, you make me want<BR>to join a PK server.  I'd think that there would be a lot more value on<BR>items and money in pk servers than blue servers.  <P></FONT>There is, but more so for one's level than anything.<FONT COLOR="0000AA"><P>You would probably get more role playing out of it, and less jerks.  <P></FONT>You don't, but what roleplaying I have managed to find was of exceedingly good quality.<FONT COLOR="0000AA"><P>Almost nay quarrel may be resolved by PK'ing.  I love it.<P></FONT>If only that were so.<FONT COLOR="0000AA"><P>Already have a level 21 bard tho =(  o well, i'll check a pk server out one <BR>day, sounds fun!<P>Darroc LeAbsorberE'ci</FONT><P>----------<P>All cynicism aside, I will say that playing on Rallos Zek is quite a different experience than playing on a normal server.  After switching to Luclin for a while, it took me the longest time not to panic whenever I heard the sound of someone casting a spell nearby.<P>Anyway, I tried playing on Rallos once just to prove to myself that it wasn't for me, and it ended up being my favorite server for a long, long time.  To anyone who hasn't tried it yet, I highly recommend giving it a day or two just to see what happens.  You may surprise yourself.  A few others may surprise you, too.<P>Here's another inquiring letter...<P>----------<P><FONT COLOR="0000AA">I read your article on PKing on Rallos Zek... This piqued my interest, as I <BR>apparently have had the wrong impression of things... I'm assuming you've <BR>played on a PvP server a lot, how often do you get attacked?  <P></FONT>That depends greatly on your play style.  If you're really into grouping, you'll get the occasional greedy soul who will prey on you when the chips are down, but usually not so often that it becomes annoying.  If you like going solo, be prepared for an attempt on your life at the very least daily (real time).  If you hang out in the more populated zones, adjust that figure accordingly.<FONT COLOR="0000AA"><P>If I create a charecter there, will I constantly be dying(moreso than already), <BR>or is it just a side bit? i.e. Do I have to PK to get decent exp, or can I simply <BR>play on that server just as normal and PK only in certain situations[?]<P></FONT>As a newbie, expect to be attacked a <I>lot</I>.  It calms down to a dull roar after a while, but ultimately the danger never ends, even for level 50+.<P>And as far as player killing for experience goes, abandon that idea - you don't gain experience or skill increases for fighting other player characters.<FONT COLOR="0000AA"><P>(despite what you said, I do RP on normal servers sometimes, and the major <BR>appeal to me about PvP servers is the freedom to kill a Teir'Dal when I'm <BR>playing a High Elf... but at the same time I will say "Remove your sorry Teir'Dal <BR>hide from my sight, or I'll remove it for you!")  <BR> <P>I haven't played on a PvP server, and I want to know if it's worth my time to <BR>start doing so... <P> -Erik Tollerud</FONT><P>----------<P>As I said above, it's well worth your time to try it out.  Nothing says you have to stay if it gets to be too tedious.  I wish you the best of luck, Erik!<P>Here is something of an informative letter based on another Rallos Zek player's point-of-view that you and others may find enlightening...<P>----------<P><FONT COLOR="0000AA">Hello Shadoe. <P>I just wanted to let you know that I truly enjoyed reading the article you <BR>wrote for the Vault Network titled The Reality of Player Killing.  I also <BR>play on Rallos Zek, and as you, I have played here for quite some time.  In <BR>fact, I have been a resident of Rallos Zek since the server was first created <BR>in Beta, and have been there ever since, in one life form or another. <P>At times, I have become disenchanted with the server, and I leave to try out <BR>one of the non-PvP server, only to find myself bored, frustrated, and <BR>returning to Rallos Zek.  I have found that the friendly Rallos Zek citizens <BR>are much more friendly then other servers, and I have also found that the <BR>PvP aspect keeps prices a bit more in check. <P>The hard part for me is I'm a warrior, and although I've been playing for <BR>quite some time, I'm still only level 22.  I'm not a power-gamer, and being <BR>a warrior - the smallest item stolen causes a lot of time and money to be <BR>wasted.... and believe me when I tell you have I have had many an item <BR>stolen.. <P>But..  I still remain loyal to Rallos Zek, in fact he is my chosen diety. <BR>The benefits do out weigh the negatives, and I know one day I will truly <BR>find a group of friends I can count on. <P>Anyway, I don't mean to bore you - I'm sure you are getting a lot of email <BR>that I should let you get back to.  Thank you for taking the time to listen, <BR>and perhaps I will see you in the world of Rallos Zek sometime.  Give me a <BR>/tell - I'm always open to making a new friend. <P>Sincerely, <P>- Myani, Fair-haired follower of Rallos Zek <P>:-)</FONT><P>----------<P>Thank you for writing in, Myani.  For a worshipper of Rallos Zek, you sure don't seem the aggressive type.  A pleasant surprise, for more reasons than one.  ; )<P>* Shadoe munches on his Salsa Verde Doritos, pondering the issue at hand.<P>Well... back to the player-killer submissions.  This one makes some excellent points I thought were interesting.  Here's a segment...<P>----------<P><FONT COLOR="0000AA">[...]  Some issues you didn't address that you might want to mention:<P>sold accounts:  should the reputation follow the account even though the<BR>new owner has no intention of being a PK?<P></FONT>As unfair as this sounds for the poor bastard who spent his money, I'd still stand my ground.  We have no guarantee that this account was actually sold to a whole new person, and frankly the thought that the player-killer who took my savant's cap actually made a real-life profit off of it sickens me... and it sickens my dog as well.<FONT COLOR="0000AA"><P>zone camping/portal camping:  you only mentioned having a problem with<BR>being killed while linkdead or bugged, how about being torn apart by ice<BR>comets (or any relevant spell) the instant you appear while zoning?<BR><P></FONT>The ability of one player to defeat another player who is helpless to run away or retaliate due to an otherworldly cause will always be on my S-list.  I just used the linkdead/stuck circumstances as examples of what happened to me in the past.  (And yes, I did cry foul.  One of them was even nice enough to apologize and repay me.)<FONT COLOR="0000AA"><P>roleplaying attacks in hostile towns:  there are some zones that can be<BR>considered fair game for race based attacks, such as a group of lightskins<BR>killing guards inside Oggok.  By nature of where they are, they are<BR>inviting the defenders of Oggok (Ogres, Dark Elves) to attack them on<BR>sight.  Any opinions on this?<P></FONT>Oh sure, everything is contextual.  If there is a raid taking place, I certainly don't begrudge any of the invaders their right to kill me, and I can't imagine they would take issue with my right to kill them in defense of my homeland and my own life.  If a high elf comes roaming along through Nektulos Forest, you bet I wholeheartedly support a quick and decisive execution in true-blue Teir'Dal fashion.  Nektulos is supposed to be feared and considered dangerous by all light dwellers, in my own humble opinion.  Had I my way, such a thing would exemplify the spirit of PvP combat on Rallos Zek.<FONT COLOR="0000AA"><P>Hope to see more people like you in game.  I've been meeting some of them<BR>but they're hard to come by.<P>Yorloc<BR>50 Necromancer<BR>Member of Fearful Symmetry<BR></FONT><P>----------<P>Thanks, Yorloc.  All this talk is making me pine for my old characters... I may be returning to Rallos sometime soon.  Until then, be strong and don't let anyone tell you you're a hedonistic necrophile! <P>Here is a most disturbing letter I received...<P>----------<P><FONT COLOR="0000AA">I agree with just about everything except the roleplay section.  I'll consider <BR>myself and my friends 'normal' for the next statement.  Normal, non-pk, <BR>players pretty seem to only fight for 2 main reasons.  Fighting a pk or <BR>fighting someone your character isn't supposed to like.   Fighting a pk is <BR>obvious.   The second reason, fighting someone your character would attack<BR>in roleplay, you invalidate as a good reason to attack someone.  What's left <BR>for the 'normal' folks?<BR> <P>So I'm now curious, without pk's and if everyone followed the spirit of your <BR>post, when would you fight another player?  If you say only when dueling and <BR>both parties agree, then i will say "go to a blue server"  ;-)   <P>And while you're at it, tell me honestly, how much fun you've had chasing <BR>some idiot DB member all over Norrath.  I've done it alot.  Nothing my guild <BR>enjoys more than a 'hunt'.  Nice equipment means so much to RZ players <BR>because it CAN be taken.  Would accomplishments feel as good if there was <BR>less standing in your <BR>way? <P>KrayvexWild Hunt</FONT><P>----------<P>The reason this letter disturbs me is because it's obviously written by someone who is used to rational thought, but still didn't quite "get" the gist of my editorial.  That tells me the fault is mine for not putting across my point clearly enough.<P>So, I'll say it again.  There is every reason in the world for PvP combat.  I support it to the very bottom of my shoes to the top of my pointy head.  My objection is when player-killers think it makes sense to reap the advantages of being a senseless, marauding murderer without accepting the de facto social consequences.  If my article was about getting rid of player-killers, believe me it would be titled something very different, and probably something overtly vulgar.  But I don't think that way, so it won't be happening.<P>This next one is from a fellow writer colleague who decided to extend the courtesy of another player-killer viewpoint...<P>----------<P><FONT COLOR="0000AA">Hey Shadoe, I wrote an entire article on newbie pking awhile back. EQstratics <BR>put it up, but the Vault wouldn't. I think you'd like this, if you are going to <BR>write a corollary to your pking article feel free to lambast mine. I think you'll <BR>find I am both conscienceless and humorous in here. Its really quite strange, I <BR>am a National Merit Scholar, 1500 SAT etc., but all I do in EQ is kill newbies <BR>like 10 times in a row until they quite the game forever. Read this, print it up or <BR>portions of it in your column and flame me! It'll be fun! <P>Fearelemental, lvl 5 <BR>GF newbie PK, Rallos Zek<BR></FONT><P>---------<P>While his article is certainly at odds with my own opinions on more than one level, I thought it was well-written, and an excellent resource for anyone who wanted to get into the business of wanton destruction and bloodshed.  Sadly, he sent me the article itself and no address to link to it.<P>Fear... if you see this, please send me the URL where you posted your article, and I'll have our host Aurum place it right &gt;HERE&lt;.<P>Here's another good player-killer counterpoint...<P>----------<P><FONT COLOR="0000AA">I agree with most, if not all of these points made.<P>However, the one I have a slight problem with is the one on Roleplaying.  I<BR>play 2 characters on Tallon Zek, one a Rogue, the other a Warrior. As both, I<BR>have had the annoyance of having someone kill me when I have low HP or are in<BR>a fight with something else.<BR><P>However, how exactly are you supposed to Roleplay as a Rogue then? As my<BR>Warrior, I have had a Rogue come up to me and kill me while I was weak. I<BR>just took it to be roleplaying, and ignored it for the most part.<BR>As my Rogue, I've killed people who were low on life a few times before.<BR>However, I usually don't take anything besides money, as my consience won't<BR>allow it (some Rogue I am). Also, I only kill once, not<BR>stay-at-their-bind-point-and-kill-them-hundreds-of-times. Is this so bad? If<BR>so, then how should I do it? Asking them wouldn't work, not only would i get<BR>killed, it wouldn't make much sense (Can I please Rob you blind? Oh, yes,<BR>please do.)<P>If you have a better way, then by all means, I'm willing to listen, as it's<BR>annoying when you're level 2 & manage to fund a bow & arrows then lose the<BR>bow & arrows.<P>And yes, I realize that I have made quite a few enemies. I've even met a<BR>high-elven wizard who's friend I insulted so much that she killed herself<BR>twice so she would be in my level range. heh. But I expected this type of<BR>thing to happen, who likes a Rogue? i'm not going to /petition a GM *so and<BR>so just killed me! WAAAH!*<P>(Quick note: Most of these things happened before the coin-only switch, now<BR>this isn't as much of an annoyance, but still valid)</FONT><P>----------<P>Ah, the life of a rogue.  The subterfuge.  The mystery.  The bane of the unwary.<P>Again, it's all contextual.  However, it's still another pitfall for the way you choose to play.  I'm not making this up - people will hate you as a player-killer, and as their assassinator besides.  Not because I say so, but just <I>because</I>.  If you kill someone and they get all upset, it's certainly not because they read this article, I can assure you.  More likely, they don't have a clue who this obscure "Shadoe" guy is in the first place.<P> "Is this so bad?"  You tell me.  Ask the victim the same question and see what kind of response you get.  If they take it all in stride, then I see absolutely nothing wrong with it.  If they get upset and start shouting warnings about your actions and calling you all manner of uncouth names and you shrug it off, I still see nothing wrong with it.  If, however, you complain about their reaction and their opinion of you and carry on about how nobody in the zone will trade with you, then I very much see a problem - as it's your due as a devious assassin.<P>Anyway, think about it.<P>Well, if you've made it this far in the reader responses, count yourself among the elite.  I don't know that I would have!  I'll leave on a positive note from a very noteworthy guild that I belonged to briefly...<P>----------<P><FONT COLOR="0000AA">As player on Rallos Zek, and the member of an anti-pk guild (Knights of<BR>Brightblade) I just have to say that is probably the best work on PK'ing<BR>I have ever read! I agree solidly with every point. I have told other<BR>before in-game the same things. Really, this is excellent work!<BR><P>Kambic, 12th Rogue<BR>Canbik, 15th Rogue<BR></FONT><P>----------<P>The Knights of Brightblade are a wonderful group of people devoted to champion the cause of those who fall victim to the roving murderers of Norrath.  I am honored to have been ranked among them at one time before leaving Rallos Zek.  If you'd like to know more about the Knights and their stalwart allies, click <A HREF=http://knightsofbrightb.tripod.com/>here</A> and take a gander.<P>Once again, I wish to thank everyone who took the time to write in their praises and contentions, and not just those I posted here.  You all make me a better writer, you're the reason I write, and I'll do my best to keep your faith.<P>Goodbye for now, and gods bless!<P>- &lt;Shadoe&gt;

<!-- End Content -->
</SPAN>
