<SPAN CLASS="pagesub">Uber Guards on PvP Servers</SPAN><br>
<img src="/images/topback.jpg" valign="bottom" width=475 height=2><br>
<SPAN CLASS="credit">Author:</SPAN> 
<span class="credit2">Tallondrakae Darktide  (<a href="mailto:N/A" class="credit2">N/A</a>)</SPAN>&nbsp;&nbsp;  
<SPAN CLASS="credit">Organization:</SPAN> <a href="" class="credit2">Blood Faith</a><br>

<SPAN CLASS="regtext">
<!-- Begin Content -->
<P>
<b><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/message_flat.asp?topic=5676533&replies=0"><center>Discuss and Debate This Issue</center></a></b><br><br>Greetings my name is Tallondrakae Darktide,<br><br>I am the leader of a guild known as Blood Faith on Rallos Zek. The reason<br>for ths post is to bring up the issue of the what I feel, are WAY<br>over-buffed guards now running rampant in Norrath. I can understand the need<br>to buff Guards on the blue servers, where mostly powergamers and powerlvlers<br>seem to congregate. <br><br>However to implement such UBER-guards onto the PVP servers, seriously<br>hinders the PVP experience. Sacking a city was next to impossible in the<br>first place. Now it is simply not possible. I can understand the validity<br>the Verant does not want people to Camp Guards to get to lvl 60. However<br>this can be avoided by just taking away the experience from killing a guard.<br><br>One of the largest glory filled wants in PVP is to have a guild strong<br>enough that can possible raid a city, and take over for a day. Some might<br>complain that this is not fair. And that newbies would be hindered.<br><br>Chances are that newbies will be too low for the invading army to hurt,<br>and secondly. When you log onto PVP, know that you are jumping into a war.<br>PVP was implemented (IMHO) to allow roleplayers, to actively roleplay the<br>conflicts between their God's, Races, Guilds, and whatnot. With Uber-Guards<br>this is seriously hindered. I hate to see our PVP server turn blue ever so<br>slowly.<br><br>Any comments and suggestions to Verant would be appreciated.<br><br><b><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/message_flat.asp?topic=5676533&replies=0"><center>Discuss and Debate This Issue</center></a></b><br>

<!-- End Content -->
</SPAN>
<a name="newsitem958660199,57860,"></a>
<SPAN CLASS="pagesub">GMs in Player Organizations</SPAN><br>
<img src="/images/topback.jpg" valign="bottom" width=475 height=2><br>
<SPAN CLASS="credit">Author:</SPAN> 
<span class="credit2">Brennos Oakkeep  (<a href="mailto:clankman@yahoo.com" class="credit2">clankman@yahoo.com</a>)</SPAN>&nbsp;&nbsp;  
<SPAN CLASS="credit">Organization:</SPAN> <a href="http://www.pcsonline.com/users/boon/koeo.htm" class="credit2">Keepers of Oak</a><br>

<SPAN CLASS="regtext">
<!-- Begin Content -->
<P>
<center><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/message_flat.asp?topic=5664567&replies=0"><b>Debate and Discuss this Article</b></a></center><br><br>Gordon says:<UL><I>"...but GMs and Guides are not allowed to belong to<br>player guilds, and player's aren't allowed to belong<br>to GM/Guide guilds. <br><br>If you have any specific information, such as server,<br>names, etc., feel free to email me (gwrinn@verant.com)<br>and I'll be happy to look into it further."</i></UL>Ok, I have always been one of those Verant supporters,<br>but this is just flat out wrong or Gordon is out of<br>touch with what's going on and needs to hush up. I<br>don't know about GM/Guide Favoritism but I do know<br>MANY guides that are in guilds and know of GMs that<br>have been in guilds too. Maybe Gordon means with their<br>GM/Guide character, but I know they have secondary<br>characters in guilds.<br><br>May get in trouble saying this, but The Rathe's old<br>GM, now even higher in the ladder, used to have a<br>character that was in a Guild (may have been an<br>officer too). I even heard rumors about her possibly<br>becoming guild leader. How do I know this? It was<br>pretty common knowledge, I think every big guild<br>leader on the Rathe knew about it, no, it wasn't my<br>guild. Although I don't think her power was ever<br>abused, there was a lot of times when friends and<br>acquiantances would send me /tells while waiting to<br>get their guild tags replaced (after that evil bug hit<br>again), wondering if she was playing instead of<br>working on it, commenting about how her guild got heir<br>guild tags back pretty fast, etc. Many spoke negativly<br>about her because of this, although I judge a person<br>by their actions, and she was always quick to help<br>when needed, and I never had a negative experience<br>with her. I still think it impacted negatively upon<br>her image to many people.<br><br>How many guides would Verant lose if they weren't<br>allowed to have their other characters in guilds?? I<br>am not a guide because I don't have the time to split<br>between the guild, RL and being one, but if I was, you<br>better believe I'd still want to be in a guild with my<br>main character and if need be, no one would know about<br>it. But if they said, "you can't be a guide and be in<br>a guild," they would be guide-less.<br><br>I do feel strongly that GMs, PAID Verant employees<br>should not be in guilds, not even with a secondary<br>character. I think the temptation is too much. I'm<br>sure being "undercover" would allow them to see things<br>going on, but don't they have the ability to drift<br>invisibly anywhere, listening into any conversation<br>anyway?<br><br>Brennos Oakkeep<br>Guild Leader<br>Keepers of Oak<br><a href="http://www.pcsonline.com/users/boon/koeo.htm">http://www.pcsonline.com/users/boon/koeo.htm</a><br>and<br>Elder Druid<br>The Rathe Druid Council<br><a href="http://www.pcsonline.com/users/boon/Druid.html">http://www.pcsonline.com/users/boon/Druid.html</a><br>and<br>Organizer<br>The Campaign to Stop Noobie Beggars<br><a href="http://www.pcsonline.com/users/boon/noob.html">http://www.pcsonline.com/users/boon/noob.html</a><br><br><center><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/message_flat.asp?topic=5664567&replies=0"><b>Debate and Discuss this Article</b></a></center>

<!-- End Content -->
</SPAN>
