<SPAN CLASS="pagesub">Problems With Iksar Faction</SPAN><br>
<img src="/images/topback.jpg" valign="bottom" width=475 height=2><br>
<SPAN CLASS="credit">Author:</SPAN> 
<span class="credit2">Kurt  (<a href="mailto:kheiden@earthlink.net" class="credit2">kheiden@earthlink.net</a>)</SPAN>&nbsp;&nbsp;  
<SPAN CLASS="credit">Organization:</SPAN> <a href="" class="credit2">N/A</a><br>

<SPAN CLASS="regtext">
<!-- Begin Content -->
<P>
<center><b><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/message.asp?mes=5533878">Discuss Issue on the Boards</a></b></center><br><br>The new faction changes going into effect for Iksar are completely<br>inappropriate.<br><br>I run the guild known as The Horde on Rallos Zek.  This server was the first<br>to instigate race wars, and there have been many great role players on that<br>server since it started.  It wasn't long until the masses established that<br>kin slaying is not an accepted practice (many are still punished severely<br>for doing this among the dark races).  It also quickly became apparent among<br>the dark races, that we were (and still are) severely outnumbered!<br><br>Perhaps I misunderstood, but I thought the introduction of the Iksar as a<br>dark race was to help create a more balanced system.  Now we're being told<br>that the Iksar are "neutral"?  Why?!  I don't understand.  This creates even<br>more imbalances in the system than before!<br><br>9 light races + 3 dark races = an unfair advantage for the pale skins and no<br>advantage for Iksar.  The Iksar will now have no impact at all in the<br>outcome of dark/light relations, and will be hunted for being neither.<br><br>To conclude, I think this is the biggest faction mistake in EQ history.<br>Dark race guilds are now faced with even more overwhelming odds in raids<br>(Iksar just get in the way), and on RZ they have no option to transfer their<br>characters over to TZ or VZ.  Even if they did, I'm told by a guide today<br>that these factions are the same on ALL servers, so there's no point in<br>moving.  <br><br>The Iksar are now faced with no allies (if they role play based on Verant's<br>factions), and cannot bank anywhere but in their home.  Now that I've wasted<br>a week of my life getting an Iksar character up to speed, my guild can't<br>invite her to join in hunting the light dwellers with our dark race guild<br>because our own Ogre bouncers will slay her.  Why would they do something so<br>drastically improper and damaging to dark races?  Please join me in telling<br>Verant that the Iksar should be allied with Trolls, Ogres, and Dark Elves,<br>AGAINST the 9 light races!<br><br>Kurt (player of Otho - Kaptain uv Da Horde)  <br><br><center><b><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/message.asp?mes=5533878">Discuss Issue on the Boards</a></b></center>

<!-- End Content -->
</SPAN>
