<img src="/images/topback.jpg" valign="bottom" width=475 height=2><br>
<SPAN CLASS="credit">Author:</SPAN> 
<span class="credit2">Negas  (<a href="mailto:caastone@networktel.net" class="credit2">caastone@networktel.net</a>)</SPAN>&nbsp;&nbsp;  
<SPAN CLASS="credit">Organization:</SPAN> <a href="" class="credit2">N/A</a><br>

<SPAN CLASS="regtext">
<!-- Begin Content -->
<P>
I am a member of a respectable guild on the Brell Server called Order of Kynigos. My name is Negas or at least used to be. I have never had to deal with a GM or guide before, so this situation both infuriates and confuses me.<br> <br>I was at the wedding of two of our guild members on Saturday 4-16 and during the reception a Senior Guide, Sinanie, asked to talk to me. She said that my name, Negas, was in violation of Verant's naming rules and that I had to change it. She said it was a commonly known name from Star Trek. Now, I don't really care for Star Trek, but I have a guild mate and my best friend are Star Trekie's. My best friend said that the closest reference to Negas in Star Trek was "The Grand Nagus Zek" in less than 10 episodes of Star Trek DS9.<br> <br>First my name isn't the same as "The Grand Nagus Zek" and secondly "The Grand Nagus" part of his name is a title not a name. It's kinda like "President of the United States Bill Clinton". She said it was too close to the spelling of Nagus and she gave me the name Nesg. I have attempted to escalate this wrongful doing with little to no success.<br> <br>The reason I am writing is because it doesn't appear that I will get my name back and that such a vague reference to another genre was picked out of all the ridiculous names that are in the game already (You know who you are). Even you players who thought that you picked a great fantasy role-playing name better watch out. I am sure that Verant could find your name in some other genre, book, movie, TV show, or something or at least a vague variation of your name.<br> <br>So watch out, you could be next!<br> <br>P.S. I just realized that the supposedly well known name Zek from Star Trek's "The Grand Nagus Zek" is used in three of Verant's servers, Rallos Zek, Tallos Zek, and Vallos Zek. Does Verant's policy that they imposed on me mean that they are going to change their server names?<br><br><CENTER><b>Discuss this issue on a special <a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/message.asp?mes=5450634">Player View Board Thread</a></b></CENTER>

<!-- End Content -->
</SPAN>
