<SPAN CLASS="pagesub">How to Raise Your Child - EQ Style</SPAN><br>
<img src="/images/topback.jpg" valign="bottom" width=475 height=2><br>
<SPAN CLASS="credit">Author:</SPAN> 
<span class="credit2">Carnuss   (<a href="mailto:N/A" class="credit2">N/A</a>)</SPAN>&nbsp;&nbsp;  
<SPAN CLASS="credit">Organization:</SPAN> <a href="" class="credit2">N/A</a><br>

<SPAN CLASS="regtext">
<!-- Begin Content -->
<P>
It has come to my attention that many children have been neglected by their<br>parents since the dawn of the EQ era, so I have taken it upon myself to<br>replace some of the conventional wisdom that may have been causing so many<br>tender minds to be snubbed in the past. Below are a few suggestions that I<br>have chosen to share with those of you who have children, but find that when<br>you are busy camping for your Ykesha or beating down the doors of Nagafen,<br>you just can't find time to aid the child in coming to grasps with the world<br>around them. I have detailed in this document the secrets to discarding the<br>world, and replacing it with the things most important in all our lives... <br><br>Problem: Child is curious why the sky is blue. <br><br>Solution: Inform the child that it isn't actually blue. It is made up of a<br>number of different hues that you have been able to maintain in the sky<br>because of your great video card and you have it set for double layer so<br>that it looks like clouds move independently. <br><br>Problem: Grandmother dies and child is bereaved. <br><br>Solution: Remind child that Grandma will be back. She just returned to her<br>bind point, and is likely to be back to loot her body any minute. Make sure<br>that you ask child if he would like to help Grandma get her exp back before<br>bed time as well; that generally makes the child feel wanted. <br><br>Problem: Child accidentally drops his gerbil off third floor of your house<br>after hearing that they were related to the feline family and watches with<br>dismay as the animal splatters thirty feet below. <br><br>Solution: Congratulate the child and remind it what incredibly good<br>experience gerbils are at that level. Recommend moving up to another mob<br>soon though, because gerbils will be turning green soon. <br><br>Problem: Child is horrified by water and he refuses to go to swimming<br>lessons you have arranged for him. <br><br>Solution: Comfort the child and remind him that many of his best items are<br>underwater. Assure him that there is nothing to be afraid of since he can<br>get a fishbone earring with a little patience, and he will certainly need<br>the swimming speed he can develop with his trainer before he can put that<br>earring to any real use. <br><br>Problem: Child has acted out in class and has been put into detention for<br>his actions. <br><br>Solution: Be assuring to the child and suggest that he practice his little<br>used skills while in detention. 2 hours should be more than enough time to<br>bring those troublesome trade skills into line. Be sure to provide the child<br>with some money to purchase any additional equipment that he may need to<br>pick up while practicing. <br><br>Problem: Child has difficulty in math and appears to be unlikely to pass the<br>class. <br><br>Solution: Start using mob base levels in the child's teachings. When<br>multiplying 2 x 50, refer to it as Fire Beetle x Zazamoukh and when the<br>child replies Excellent as the answer to the question, you have reached your<br>goal. The child has become better at Math (100)! <br>Problem: The child is going to a career day and is curious what path would<br>be best to get information on. <br><br>Solution: Suggest that the child avoid any careers that currently pay well.<br><br>Programmers, lawyers, doctors, network administrators, and politicians are<br>likely to get their salaries nerfed when the next patch comes out, so<br>instead encourage such engagements as brick layer, bus boy, musician, and<br>artist. All of these should be boosted considerably in the future for<br>balance. <br><br>Problem: Child is busted for fighting on school property and you are<br>contacted to pick the child up. <br><br>Solution: Reprimand the child strongly. Remind the child that if mobs are<br>aloud to escape they will come back and cause trains. Instead suggest that<br>next time the child should Snare the mob, kill it, and try to avoid letting<br>it seek help. With those types of tactics the child should be far more<br>likely to level quickly. <br><br>Problem: You discover child has been stealing from you. <br><br>Solution: Do not get angry. Try to push the child into a different center of<br>focus. Rogues are a weak class, but you can't tell a rogue to quit. Have the<br>child try killing a few things. Buff it a few times to see if it likes the<br>augmentation role. After a few short rounds of trying any other class, the<br>child is sure change its behavior immediately. <br><br>Problem: Child has killed its substitute teacher with a pencil. <br>Solution: Hire excellent lawyer to defend child from Juve under the argument<br>that it was a rare spawn and should at least be killed once to see what it<br>carries. <br><br>Problem: Child is found drinking with friends after school in your back<br>yard. <br><br>Solution: Purchase more alcohol and join them. You never know when a high<br>alcohol tolerance is going to be useful. Encourage the child and his friends<br>to drink liberally and quickly so as to see their skills rise quicker. If<br>your child has brought home an attractive teenage girl in his batch of<br>friends, make sure to encourage her to drink more than the rest and begin a<br>private tell conversation as soon as you have aided her in getting to her<br>skill cap. <br><br>Problem: Child has disappeared and you can't find its equipment. <br>Solution: Make a new child that looks just like it. Look back with fond<br>remembrance, but keep in mind, it was just one child and doesn't really<br>matter in the whole scheme of things since you can have up to 8 on your<br>account. Make sure the next one you make is a different class. <br><br>*** DISCLAIMER *** <br><br>I am not a parent currently, but I am however friends with a few parents who<br>have found this advice sound. If you choose to use any of the above methods<br>of child rearing, be wary that it does tend to cause detachment, painful<br>urination, law suits, back aches, sterility, and heavy blood loss in some<br>specimens. Check with your psychiatrist before taking any action described<br>above. If you do however find that these work for you, be sure to tell two<br>friends! <br><br>Carnuss Dire <br>Level 50 49 50 49 50 49 50 49 50 49 50 49 50 49 50 49 50 49 50 49 50 49 50<br>49 50 49 50 49 50 49 50 49 50 49 50 49 50 49 50 49 50 49 50 49 50 49 50 49<br>50 49 50 49 50 49 shaman.

