<P>
Well, it finally has happened. Rallos Zek was struck down by Roleplaying last night. I am unsure how many of you had heard of this, but I am quite appalled at what someone on the Verant Staff (including Guides and GameMasters) has done. Let me explain.<P>I like to consider myself a member of the Rallos Zek Chronicles. I lead a guild called the Elven Guard who is dedicated to killing the kinslayers and murderers in the Faydark and helping out all of our younger kin in any way we can. We also like to involve ourself with the roleplaying community of our server which resides at the Rallos Zek Chronicles: <a href="http://www.ralloszek.com/Roleplay/">http://www.ralloszek.com/Roleplay/</a><P>Since I began playing on RZ, I have turned to this site for my roleplaying information for the server. I have been involved with many of the battles, roleplaying events, and other PlayerRun structures. I am fairly sure that without RZ Chronicles or something like it, I would not be playing Everquest today. You can only hack up so many monsters to get loot and find it enjoyable. Holly, though, brought together everyone who wants to Roleplay on our server and we began forming events that would be fun for the entire server! We have asked Verant for help with some aspects of these but, of course, we were rarely replied to.<P>Last night, though, RZ Chronicles finally got noticed by Verant! But not in the way I would of liked and many who visit RZ Chronicles feel the same way. We have (or maybe it is had now after this fiasco) a storyline about the "Daughter of Innoruuk" which many of you know as Kallystra from the recent story in Everquest Express or her article about the "Spawn of the Deceiver" on recent Everquest newsites. Well, it appears as if Verant did not only borrow this storyline but use it on our server! They created a GM named Lanys T'Vyl who calls herself the Avatar of Hate and the true Daughter of Innoruuk. Fair enough, I am sure many were extremely agitated when they read this, but many people tried to roleplay it out. Even Kallystra was there last night, roleplaying with this GM, calling her the falsechild and heretic, since Kallystra has already been known to be the Daughter of Innoruuk. I thought I would bring to your attention a similarity that exists between this new GM run plot and one of the Straylight subplots -- the daughter of Innoruuk plotline. Just in case you haven't heard of this particular plotline, here is the link: <a href="http://www.ralloszek.com/Roleplay/Straylight/straylight.htm">http://www.ralloszek.com/Roleplay/Straylight/straylight.htm</a>. Look under the "Mahlyce's Child" heading, if you please. There you will find no less than seventeen separate links leading to various stories, posts, letters, and the like. There were numerous other posts about this plot on the various rallos zek boards that weren't archived, as well.<P>I was appalled, however, when I learned that after many roleplayers attempts to "roleplay" this situation with the GM, many were killed BY THE POWER OF THE GODS and there is even questions about the GM sending Teir'Dal Guards against one of the Teir'Dal Clerics there that followed Kallystra (which can cause experience loss). Finally, I learned that this GM "squelched" Kallystra so she could not talk in any format; not /Tell, not /G, not /Shout, and not /Say. Kallystra posted both an RP story of this and the logged text. Nowhere in either of these, does she spam, harass, use K33L DoOdZ speech, or anything that would warrant squelching. Not only did this employee of Verant use and abuse a PlayerRun Storyline but also abused his or her powers by squelching (and the other things she did are questionable too, if you ask me).<P>I am completely for GMs enhancing PlayerRun plots but I would rather have no GM help if they are just going to "borrow" and abuse currently ongoing plots and use it on the server the paying customers are running it on. If they wanted to do the Avatar of Hate on another server, I am sure many Roleplayers would feel cheated since it was their storyline, but they would not feel so bad as when it actually spoils and ruins their storyline by running it on their server.<P><b>Kallystra's Story:</b><P>My name is Kallystra, a cleric in the service of our Father Innoruuk and some say his child by ways of my mother Mahlyce. It was the day after I had heard of the False Prophet named Lanys T'Vyl. The woman who appears to be Teir'Dal and claims to be the one and only true Innoruuk's Daughter. But I know the truth. I know that she is actually the spawn of Thepa and such knowledge shall be spread to my people to save them from her blasphemous words and deeds.<P>I had awoken in the 3rd Gate after a long day of training. It appeared to be only a few hours from whence I went to sleep but something awoke me... the voices had returned.<P>"The Deceiver's Child is back" they whisper in my head over and over.<P>I grab my Hammer of Wrath, given to me by my Father Innoruuk and walk forth to teach this wench the true power of the Father.<P>When I reached the entrance of Neriak, I saw a mass of Teir'Dal and Trolls surrounding a woman. I begin to walk towards her when she says to me, "Ahhh, the falsechild."<P>This one would be tricky indeed. Using my own words against me. But it was not something I had not already expected. When one does battle with the God of Pain known as Thepa they know that tricky and deceit are his main tools.<P>I simply say, "I am the Mouth of Innoruuk."<P>Lanys T`Vyl says, "I am Innoruuk's TRUE Daughter."<P>A foolish Teir'Dal by the name of Shakrot says "This doesn't look like a mouth."<P>I say, "Nay, you are but a falsehood."<P>"Liar! Falsehood!" the spawn of Thepa screams as she besieges her father to aid her, knowing my words... my very presence would show her true self.<P>A few moments after she screamed those words, I felt the world flash before my eyes. I knew I had been struck down by the gods. Actually, one god. Thepa, the Great Deceiver of the Teir'Dal.<P>But death was not to be mine. I felt my life slip back into me... but I was no longer in the Neriak entrance. Instead, I was in my home... my father's home. The Spires of Innoruuk.<P>I quickly make my way back to the entrance. As soon as I am there, I face the falsechild again. She looks into my very soul, trying to pierce it with her father's gaze. But I knew behind that stare was a scared child. Her father was not strong enough to slay the faithful child of Innoruuk. I say to her, "Do my words scare you, falsechild? Do you fear the Teir'Dal will see through the minion of Thepa's charade? It seems that the Father has given me life again for a reason. To prove against your heresy."<P>Lanys T`Vyl says, trying to cover up who is actually striking me down, "Innoruuk shall strike you down again, Heretic!"<P>"And the true Father shall give me life again, false one. The Father is greater than your power, Minion of Thepa."<P>Again, our gazes meet. The battle of wills commences. She stares into my eyes and sees that I am my Father's child, my will indomitable.<P>"Strike me down, though, if it makes you feel better... show your weakness," I say to her.<P>One of the Father's faithful by the name of Jamaer shouts, "Lanys T'Vyl is a kinslayer!"<P>Lanys T`Vyl says, "I call upon the Lord of Hate, my Father! Strike down the false Daughter, and teach her a lesson!"<P>Another Teir'Dal comes forth, asking "Where is this newcomer with such power?"<P>I scans the skies, looking for this beam of power supposedly from Innoruuk to strike me down. None comes. "'It seems he has spoken, false one."<P>Lanys T`Vyl says, 'You are the child of the Deceiver. And you shall pay, foolish girl."<P>Meanwhile, Shakrot scratches her chin, not knowing who to believe.<P>Finally, the power of Thepa strikes me again... and again I receive life from my Father in the Church of the 3rd Gate.<P>Again, I return to the entrance. I knew I had bested her. I have spoken the truth over and over, never laying a finger upon her. The truth was my weapon in those battles and try struck deep.<P>I returned to the entrance to see Lanys T'Vyl killing many Teir'Dal. All the while yelling "Foolish Heretic!" or "None may touch me!"<P>A wise Teir'Dal by the name of Telan approaches the Deceiver's Daughter and asks, "How do we know you are who you say?"<P>She replies by only saying, "Telan, you question my powers and my heritage?"<P>He replies by saying "That I do, for anyone can protest that they are what they say."<P>I had heard enough of her blasphemy. I had seen enough of her slaying my kin in the name of her father Thepa, God of Pain. No more Teir'Dal blood would be shed!<P>I shout, "Lanys the Falsechild is a kinslayer! Would our Father Innoruuk wish his child to slay his people?! Hear the true words of the Father, not the speech of the Daughter of Thepa!"<P>But already some of the Teir'Dal had turned from the Father and had not known it. Rajaat, a young Teir'Dal says, "Not all of Innoruuk's children are loyal, and thus many must be cleansed Kallystra, The blueness of your skin does not reflect the blasphemies spewed forth from your mouth."<P>But in my defense, many Teir'Dal speak forth. One was Melisandre who said to the masses, "Kallystras words ring true in my ears! Lanys is a false prophet of our father Innoruuk."<P>Lanys T`Vyl says, "I shall prove it to you..." as she sets an icy glare upon Telan.<P>Another Teir'Dal by the name of Ayria says, "She is back..."<P>Jedig says, "Who is?"<P>Ayria says, "Kallystra."<P>Lanys T`Vyl says, "Father! Teach this mortal a lesson!"<P>But I shout to the crowd, "Who is the false child here? Lanys slays our brothers and sisters when I speak the truth... would the spawn of Innoruuk do such things?"<P>Fatallia says, "Why do you kill your own brethren Lanys?"<P>I say to Lanys, my eyes burning with the hatred of the Father, "Would you kill the children of Innoruuk again, kinslayer?"<P>Another Teir'Dal by the name of Fiilch shouts, "Who kills our kin in our homeland?"<P>"Would you kill the Father's shocktroopers of darkness?" I ask her again, waiting for a reply.<P>Azreal shouts, "The so-called spawn of Innoruuk seem all too eager to slay each other for less reason than that."<P>Again, I question her before the Teir'Dal and our allies "What have you done for our people aside from kill us?"<P>Lanys T`Vyl says, "Kallystra, you have two choices... serve or die."<P>I respond, "I have saved the masses in the NektulosI have helped stop the spawn of Thepa. I am in the Nektulos daily, healing my kin and reading them for battles. I help stop the kinslasyer."<P>But she does not answer me, just stands there, at a loss for words. The sword of truth was deep in her gut indeed. I give it another thrust...<P>I say, "You have done nothing. You slay the Teir'Dal. Not even the kinslayers, but the Father's faithful. You have even slain members of the Blood Coven who serves our Queen!"<P>Melisandre shouts, "All should know the power of our Father. We do not need her or her falsehoods to know the truth!"<P>And then another Teir'Dal questions her. Fatallia asks, "How was Giua a heretic? Why did you kill him for just questioning you?"<P>Greblik shouts, "Kazeek thool wud hab nun ub dis!"<P>Lanys T`Vyl says, "Telan, you wished proof?" as her hands fill with power, ready to strike.<P>But, before she can slay another of the faithful, I stand between them. If any would take her wrath, it would be. I say to her, "You are not the Father, your word is not law."<P>Fiilch shouts, "The will of Innoruuk is not in the hereafter, but in the present, carrying out his will upon those that his hatred is poured out on."<P>Lanys T`Vyl says, "I am the Father's emphermal hand"<P>I say, "You alone do not command who lives and dies. You are nothing but a spoiled child full of power."<P>Lanys T`Vyl says, "Innoruuk, Lord of Hate! Teach this mortal a lesson and show him your power!"<P>Fatallia says, "I do not think the father would agree with your harsh judgement."<P>Melisandre shouts, "May the father of us all bring pain and suffering upon those who listen to the falsehoods spewed forth by Lanys T'Vyl."<P>Lanys stands before me, power at her fingertips, ready to strike me. She raises for the kill when I say, "Kill me again, though. Show your true colors and allegiance. I have not raised a hand to you, child. But kill me again."<P>Fatallia says, "Lanys T'Vyl if you touch Kallystra you are abusing your powers."<P>Lanys T`Vyl says, "Kallystra, your insolence shall be silenced. Your Father who gave you speech, shall now take it away."<P>Quickly, I felt the power of Thepa the Deceiver about me. I tried to speak, but could not. I tried to yell and shout, but no words came forth. I tried to speak to those with my mind... but he even silenced that. And many have noticed that I was speaking but words would not come forth...<P>Fatallia says, "Lanys T'Vyl has let her power go to her head."<P>Azreal says, "Who is it that claims fo speak our Father's words?"<P>One of the Blood Coven's faithful by the name of Qynnralla saw the Deceiver's child about to strike another of the Father's children. Qynnralla strikes with a fury and the fight begins.<P>Many of the Teir'Dal are upon her. I cannot stand back and watch their blood spill at the hands of the Daughter of Thepa. Over and over, the Father's power of Furor strikes from my hands into Lanys's being. And when my mana was depleted, I grabbed my Hammer of Wrath and began to strike her. All around me, Teir'Dal were falling by the power of Thepa. But my will was indomitable and I fought on.<P>Lanys's few minions and followers surrounded her, trying to save her from my wrath. Spell after spell, they cast upon me but most were shrugged off. I am my Father's daughter and I would pull her blasphemous tongue from her mouth if it was the last thing I did.<P>Finally, I noticed that Lanys was not hurt. When I first saw her, I took her measure and noticed her skill was well beneath my own. But somehow, the power of furor and the might of my hammer was not harming her. I looked around me, striking those Teir'Dal that would try and stay my hand of hatred. I would fight them all to my death.<P>But one of the Father's faithful saw what I was trying to do. He was stronger than I and enchanted me to his will. He then had me run behind him, all the way to the Commons and away from harm. My blood boiled with hatred for I wanted to show the Deceiver's child and his new found minions their error of their ways in turning their back on the Father. But this Teir'Dal that saved me was wise. At the moment, it was not a battle I could win. Not alone.<P>So, when we were far enough, he tried to talk to me but I could still not reply. My words scared Thepa greatly and he did he best to make sure I would not be heard. I bowed before the brave Teir'Dal that saved me and gated to my home, the Spires of Innoruuk where I would regain my strength and my speech... and plan the downfall of the the Deceiver and his child Lanys T'Vyl.<P>Kallystra, Mouth of Innoruuk<br>"My mouth is the Mouth of Innoruuk.<br>"The Children shall not stray,<br>"The body shall not fail in His service."<P>OOC: Well, this is all actually a true event that happened on Rallos Zek in the Nektulos Forest last eve. For a long time, the roleplayers of Rallos Zek have gathered at the site called Rallos Zek Chronicles (Created and hosted by Holly Golightly.) <P>One of our player-run storylines is the "Daughter of Innoruuk" known as Kallystra, Mouth of Innoruuk. This storyline has been going on for a few months at the very least and, to my knowledge, the only such storyline on ANY of the servers. For some of our various PlayerRun events, we have asked Verant and the GMs for help in some of the PlayerRun events... perhaps have a God show up, turn off the Guards in Freeport for the Great Wars, things of that sort. But we never received any replies. Then, just yesterday, I was in Nektulos and saw Lanys T'Vyl, who had taken our storyline and plot. I decided to roleplay it out with her, incorperating her into our current storyline, "The God of Pain Thepa". I stayed In Character the entire time (I always roleplay unless I say OOC) and all the words you read in this story is what I said. What did I get for my efforts? I was squelched for atleast a half hour (after not being able to /tell, /g, /say, /shout for 30 minutes, I logged out). To me, this is an abuse of power. I did not curse. I did not use k33l DoOdZ speech. I did not spam. I roleplayed it and all I got for my efforts were a few killings from "The Power of the Gods" and then squelched. Furthermore, when she attacked me, she conned green to me. But, for all my magic spells I cast upon her, for all the times I struck her with my weapon, she could not be hurt at all. To me, yet again, another abuse. If you are going to play a powerful character, don't be a level 5 or under character that cons green to everyone but cannot be even hurt by a level 20+ character. Finally, I am disgusted with Verant's abuse of a PlayerRun plot. Those of us that visit RZ Chronicles try to put on an event for EVERYONE once a month. We have an RP side of it, where all those that wish to roleplay have a place to go and fight, and another part of it where people who want to just kill can go. Under our belts are the two Battles of Freeport, Battle of Qeynos, Invasion of Faydwer, and a few others. We have asked for GM assistance in some of these but never got a reply. Then, all of a sudden, a GM named Lanys T'Vyl shows up as the "Daughter of Innoruuk" and only on the ONE server who already has a PlayerRun Daughter of Innoruuk that is widely known. If they wanted to use the plot, fine, but do it on another server or work with us (the ones that have the plot going) instead of overrunning it without even telling us. This very same thing happened in Ultima Online on the Pacific Shard. I lived in the Endless Graveyard, the only Roleplayed City of Evil on the shard and a few powerhungry Seers came in and created characters that were suppose to be normal characters but could kill Energy Vortex's with their own hands. Most of the RPing Goods and Evils left because of this. I would love Verant to get involved with PlayerRun Events and Storylines, but I would rather not have them at all if they are going to ruin those already in effect by overrunning them. I know I will get some flames from this post, but I have MANY people that agree with me.<P>Kallystra

