<P>
<U>CALLING OUT FOR A HEALER</U><BR>By &lt;Shadoe&gt; and Timelord<BR><FONT size=-2>...with apologies to the movie <I>Footloose.</I></FONT><P>(Sung to the music of "Holding Out for a Hero"<BR>Performed by Bonnie Tyler<BR>Written by Jim Steinman and Dean Pitchford)<P>----------<P>Where have all the players gone and where are all the guards?<BR>Where's the friendly NPCs to fight the rising MOBs? <BR>Isn't there a shadow knight to taunt this orc off me?<BR>As I fight, I curse and I turn and I scream for what I need...<P>"I need a healer!"<BR>I'm calling out for a healer or I can't win the fight,<BR>He's gotta run long and he's gotta run fast,<BR>Or my corpse will be lost in the night.<BR><P>I need a healer!<BR>What I need is a healer or I'll end up in flight,<BR>He's gotta be pure, and it's gotta be soon, <BR>Or I'm gonna be losin' my life --<BR>Losin' my life.<P>Playin' after midnight in this world of fantasy,<BR>Somewhere just beyond my sight, some newbie's training onto me.<BR>Racing on like thunder, seeking something I can beat,<BR>It only takes a giant rat to knock me off my feet.<P>I need a healer!<BR>I'm prayin' hard for a healer or I won't see the light,<BR>He's gotta be good, and he's gotta be prime,<BR>So I can admire his might.<P>I need a healer!<BR>You better find me a healer, or I'll be looking to kite,<BR>He's gotta be elf, or he's gotta be dwarf, <BR>But he's gotta save me from my plight.<P>I need a healer!<BR>I'm calling out to a healer, or I can't win the fight...<P>Up where the giants meet the griffins above,<BR>Out where a_hatchling00 spits on me,<BR>I could swear there is something, somewhere stalking me.<BR>Through the lag and the kills and the pain,<BR>And the storm and the flood,<BR>I can feel death approach like a chill in the blood.<P>I need a healer! <BR>I couldn't wait for a healer, 'cuz a creature's in sight,<BR>I gotta be cured, and it's gotta be now, <BR>'Cuz my hit points are sure gettin' tight.<P>I need a healer! <BR>I gotta get me a healer, or it just won't be right,<BR>It clobbered me fast, and it clobbered me good, <BR>So he's gotta restore me to life.<BR>

