<SPAN CLASS="pagesub">Beggar Petition Reader Responses</SPAN><br>
<img src="/images/topback.jpg" valign="bottom" width=475 height=2><br>
<SPAN CLASS="credit">Author:</SPAN> 
<span class="credit2">Shadoe  (<a href="mailto:shadoe@vaultnetwork.com" class="credit2">shadoe@vaultnetwork.com</a>)</SPAN>&nbsp;&nbsp;  
<SPAN CLASS="credit">Organization:</SPAN> <a href="http://www.eqvault.com" class="credit2">EQVault</a><br>

<SPAN CLASS="regtext">
<!-- Begin Content -->
<P>
Well, it looks like I managed to hit a nerve with this article, which both gratifies me and scares me all at once.  As a writer, I'm gratified because dropping a bomb on any community never fails to boost one's outlook on life.  As an avid fan and player of EverQuest, I'm dismayed to discover that some people out there actually took the petition seriously.<P>Just to spell it out, I never thought in a million years anyone would see the Beggar Petition on a level any higher than that of being absurdly silly.  I didn't even intend it as a <I>joke</I> to fool people.  All I wanted to do was point out the absurdity of several of the petitions that have cropped up lately by making the most ludicrous, outrageous petition I could think up.<P>But satire is a very subtle medium.  As it turns out, some readers "got it" while others took it seriously; the former of which makes me happy, while the latter really just serves to prove my point... far better than I expected.  As ridiculously thick as I laid on the demands in the Beggar Petition (at least *I* considered them to be thick), there was still not enough contrast between it and other genuine petitions out there.  Some people took it as being totally on the level, and to me that says a <I>lot</I> about the laughability of those genuine petitions I'm attacking.<P>Do I think all the petitions being composed are full of tripe?  Of course not.  But, naming no names, I have come across several that make me blink and shake my head.  All that remains now is the fear that I may have given some of those absurd-petition-makers some new ingredients to add to their boiling cauldron of bright ideas.<P>So, without further ado, I'll proceed to post some of the many reader responses that caught my eye, along with the occasional response by yours truly.<P>----------<P><FONT COLOR="#000080">HAHAHAHAHAHAHA<BR>your such a funny guy, this is so funny <BR>HAHAHAHAHAHAHA<BR>you have some imagination kid<BR><P>beggars are scum, I kill every one I see , maybe ill be able to kill you.<BR>oh god sorry ,was thinking this might happen , But the developers will have a<BR>good laugh when they see this. hehe <BR>it's a good thing you trying to make them laugh like that, relive some of <BR>there stress hehe.<P>PS:  If your serious , your either one messed up kid or don't belong inEQ</FONT><P>----------<P>...and then there were those who weren't quite sure what to make of it.  It had just enough believability to make them question their own rationale.<P>The beggars of Norrath rub me the wrong way, too.  Every time I hear someone asking for a handout, it smacks to me of meaning that their needs are somehow above my own.  I'm sorry, but when any fool character can go out and get that magical gold coin by hunting down a few newbie creatures and selling their various body parts (the creatures', not the character's), the beggar's clout really just falls flat on its tucus.<P>And as far as Verant staff goes, a part of me does hope it got circulated among the dev team, because they really do deserve whatever stress relief they can get.  I flatter myself, but I just hope I didn't alarm any of them into sebuku.<P>These next couple, however, were forwarded to me by Aurum.  Visionary that he is, he saw fit to create a posting in the news area that furthered the illusion that this petition was the real deal.  As you can see, our combined efforts managed to set off some very alarmed readers...<P>----------<P><FONT COLOR="#000080">I honestly cannot believe that you would post something like that.  Did you <BR>even read what was written in that petition.  Now I am all for free speech, but this one just takes the cake :).  Hehe my bet is that one will be the laughing stock at Varrant.. They will post it as one of the most rediculas posts ever..  I have come to this board for a long time and have always respected everyones posts.  Some are very funny some are informative but this one is just assinine.  Well thankyou for you time and please understand these are only my thoughts</FONT><P>----------<FONT COLOR="#000080"><P>First and formost let me express my congrats on a fine job that the staff of eqvault has done. I am a frequent visiter, and love the content. I am writeing in responce to the outrageious new petition of the begging class. I would have mailed this to the riter, but his webpage isnt working.<P></FONT>Allow me to interject here, and mention that <a href="http://www.pitchinthebush.com">http://www.pitchinthebush.com</a> is, so far as I know, a totally bogus URL.<P><FONT COLOR="#000080">Before I begin, did you read the petition? If not, please do because non of this will make since. I have been  true dnd fan for a long time, and I have seen all kinds of things. In a world where dragons excisted and magic was present, beggers had a place too? Even so, would they become nothing more then a begger? Certainly not a mighty warrior, or a magic caster. Simply put in the 20th century, "a bum". That is somthing we do not need for this, or any other roleplaying game. Need I say more, the askings of the petition are outrageious. Have the ability to cast spells and to do high level spells only wizards can do? This would not only imbalance the game, furthermore, make it look like a joke. Let me sum up this little rant by saying it was not a petition, more likely a not so funny joke. I would also like to say whoever posted the petition did not read it. If they had they would see the sillyness and stupidness of the entire thing. I would request the next time eqvault would review the petition more closer before letting it sit on the page making yourselfs look bad. Thankyou for your time-</FONT><P>----------<P>Now don't I feel like "Weird Al" Yankovic after spoofing Coolio?<P>Believe me, it wasn't meant as a joke.  I was merely pointing out absurdity by being absurd.  Still, I think someone needs to their valium.<P>Look at these guys, f'rinstance...<P>----------<P><FONT COLOR="#000080">All I can say is..... ROFLMAO!!<P>That was great. I've been a big fan of your columns for some time now, keep up the good work. Someone needs to point out the idiocies of this game society. =)</FONT><P>----------<P><FONT COLOR="#000080">The beggar's petition is one of the most spot on (not to mention funny!!) <BR>EQ related items I have read to date...<BR>Thanks!<BR>Caldara, Monk of the 14th circle <BR>(maybe I can get those azure sleeves by tonight if I really get down and<BR>snivel, grovel and whine!)<BR></FONT><P>----------<P><FONT COLOR="#000080">That was great, until i went into Shadoe's Corner i thought you were serious.</FONT><P>----------<P>What pleasant, well-adjusted members of society.  ; )<P>This last response I saved because the author took the time to nitpick every ridiculously insane item one-by-one.  Anyone with the time to go about doing such a thing is either a very dedicated EQ fan, or a total loon -- which is an admittedly fine line.  (So, what does that say about someone who sits down to write whole articles about it?)<P>----------<P><FONT COLOR="#000080">First of all. Sorry, I dont want to hurt your idea of this beggar class, butI just could resist trying to take you down from whatever clouds you live on:-)<BR>Please dont take any personal offence by my replies. [added later on] Thisis a joke, right? If it is, skip the rest :-)<P></FONT>Are you kidding?  I wouldn't miss this for all the tribbles in Star Trek.<P><FONT COLOR="#000080">I think you dont know what you're demanding here. Creating a whole new classas perfectly balanced as the others before next patch. Are you nuts? Theymight be able to implement it in the expansion pack if you're lucky.</FONT><P>Oh, come on!  It's just a few teensy weensy lines of code and some token creativity thrown in for good measure!  Are you seriously saying that they couldn't implement a beggar class by Friday?  If not, they don't deserve their jobs!  Forget it!  I'm quitting EQ forever!  If I can't have my beggar class, then the entire game is just unplayable!<P><FONT COLOR="#000080">If you are lazy and dont want to earn your items by hard work you reallyshouldnt play EQ. I assure you that Verant wont give away free items likethat, its NOT good for the economy.</FONT><P>Oh yeah?  Well, a good economy stems from everyone having lots of money!  Ha!  Beat that!  That's right...<P><FONT COLOR="#000080">Can you even imagine how it would be with a public broadcast command? Everbeen to Greater Faydark? Its the most populated zone in Norrath and I hatebeing there because of all the spamming in the chat window. It just wonthappen. Forget it.</FONT><P>You don't think so?  Well I happen to be a personal friend of Brad's and he told me at lunch the other day that they were seriously considering it!  In fact, he's going to get me a job at Verant as their number one ideas person, because I know everything there is to know about EQ... and stuff!<P><FONT COLOR="#000080">Spirit of Wolf on a beggar? Its a spell connected to the spirit world. Howare you linking beggars to natural people like Druids and Shamans? Teleport,maybe, but that would create a completely out of the fantasy world we havehere. Which brings me to another point. Every class in Norrath wheather youwant it or not has as a goal to become wealthy, except maybe the Monks. Icant just imagine a lvl47 beggar who has around 10000 pp on his bankaccount. One way to solve this is to change the experience-system so thatbeggar only can get XP from money they give to their guildmasters. But thatwont happen, its way too much recoding needed from the developers.</FONT><P>Is not!!!<P><FONT COLOR="#000080">This is not a civilized culture, this is a massive multiplayer onlineroleplaying game.</FONT><P>Is too!!!<P><FONT COLOR="#000080">Why should you be able to carry more? No other class getprivilieges/penalties in this issue. I doubt they will change that.</FONT><P>We already told you why!  Open your eyes and read our petition, you blind fool!  We also need the ability to put containers within containers... just to be on the safe side!  Hey, UO does it, and that game ROX!<P><FONT COLOR="#000080">This is getting funny. Maybe this whole thing is a joke. Let me know.</FONT><P>You'll be talking out the other side of your mouth when Verant sees our petition and implements our ideas!!!  We already have FIFTEEN names on the list, and that's after only ONE WEEKEND!  Beat that, bucko!<P><FONT COLOR="#000080">Owe you? You bougt their game. They make the rules. And their rule is to getas many players as possible without lifting a hand. I also hate that factbut there is absolutely nothing we can do about that.We agreed to their policy, their terms, their... game. Gee man they are gamedevelopers not Gods.</FONT><P>So you agree with us!  YES!  Make that SIXTEEN names!!!  We got Verant by the stones now, man!<P><FONT COLOR="#000080">Ban me? why? I didnt harrass you or even talked to you in game. This is anormal e-mail reply. From this point of view I'm not even an EQ accountholder. I really really hope this is a joke. I cant even understand howsomething like this can come from the Vaultnetwork. I know might be talkinga bit over my head now, but I'm trying to help you, not hurt you.<P>IF this IS a joke.. you have really fooled me nicely. And I hope you had agood laugh. I just didnt like the joke.</FONT><P>----------<P>Well, that's your privilege.<P>Personally, all I care about is making my point, and you've done a fabulous job in delivering it for me. In a nutshell: <I>let's tone down the petitions to the dull roar of common-sense.</I>  I've seen petitions -- real, honest-to-god petitions -- demanding incredible things like rogues wearing full plate armor and wizards with healing spells.  Apparently there are others out there that are so outrageous as to make this Beggar Petition seem viable by comparison.<P>I've also seen many petitions with insightful and well thought out ideas that I'm hoping manage to make their way to the right person's desk  at Verant.  I just pity the poor souls who are assigned the task of going through them all and seperating the wheat from the tares, as it were.  >From where I'm sitting, their sainthood is guaranteed.<P>By the way, a long-time imponderable of mine has been answered with the latest EQX Q&A column: does the begging skill really work?  I also thought the ad for the Fit to Print section was humorously appropriate!  Check it out at <A HREF="http://eqx.simplenet.com/Issue86/iss86.htm">http://eqx.simplenet.com</A>.<P>At any rate, my thanks goes out to those of you who took the time to write in; praises and condemnations alike!<P>- &lt;Shadoe&gt;<P><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">("...the ability to cast SoW on ourselves..."  Hehe!  Sometimes I just kill me...)</FONT>

<!-- End Content -->
</SPAN>
