<SPAN CLASS="pagesub">Beggar Petition</SPAN><br>
<img src="/images/topback.jpg" valign="bottom" width=475 height=2><br>
<SPAN CLASS="credit">Author:</SPAN> 
<span class="credit2">Shadoe  (<a href="mailto:shadoe@vaultnetwork.com" class="credit2">shadoe@vaultnetwork.com</a>)</SPAN>&nbsp;&nbsp;  
<SPAN CLASS="credit">Organization:</SPAN> <a href="http://www.eqvault.com" class="credit2">EQVault</a><br>

<SPAN CLASS="regtext">
<!-- Begin Content -->
<P>
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2><B>Beggars of Norrath unite!!!</B></FONT></CENTER><P>It is time for us to stand up and demand to be heard!  We have remained silent long enough about the despicable conditions under which Verant expects us to play, and as paying customers we shouldn't have to take it anymore!  So, please read through this petition and add your name to dozens of others who have joined our cause!<P>For one thing, Verant, GIVE US OUR OWN CLASS!  It's an obvious oversight, and we expect it to be rectified IMMEDIATELY with the next patch!  This is a MUST, Verant.  If not implemented, then you will find yourselves penniless because we're all going to cancel our accounts!<P>But that alone won't fix the game for us!  Once our Beggar class is established, not only do we want to start out with a standard begging skill of AT LEAST 50 (which we rightly deserve), but we want additional begging-type skills.  Name ideas include wimpering, pleading, grovelling, all the way up to shameless brown-tonguing.  Each progressive skill will have the potential to extract an even greater sum of money from NPC's, not to mention magic items and unique artifacts!<P>When it comes to begging from other players, we need to be able to /shout our pleas for money and items across the ENTIRE SERVER, instead of just one zone!  At BEST, we can only beg from about 100 players at a time, and this makes the Beggar class TOTALLY unplayable, and at a disadvantage to EVERY other class!<P>What follows, naturally, is the ability to cast SoW on ourselves so we can travel across Norrath to people willing to twink- erm... to make donations.  Without this, it would take forever to run across all the zones when we get a /tell from someone on the other side of the map, and that just makes NO sense!  Teleport would be even better, but that's a play balance issue you can work out internally.<P>Next, we must have the ability to steal from anyone who might suggest we go out and earn our keep!  We have to show them that we have NO other way to make a living in a fruitless world where NO opportunities exist to get ahead.  Such cruelty must be met with justice, and this is the ONLY way to do it!  Besides, they all owe us all that stuff anyway!  Who ever heard of a civilized culture without an open-ended welfare system??<P>We also demand that Verant give us a boost to carrying weight versus strength.  Plus, we need more slots in our bank accounts!  Our occupation requires that we are able to have lots more unstackable items than other classes, so that's something else we need.<P>Of course, it goes without saying we should be able to wear full plate armor, since everyone else will be after our stuff on the +PvP server!  We must be given SOME chance to survive!  Invisibility would be nice, too, but we're willing to compromise on this one.<P>Lastly, we request that Verant set up a policy that bans players who react to our pleas for handouts with cruel responses, like "Get a job, deadbeat," and "Go kill some bats, newbie!"  These verbal attacks are uncalled for and disrupt the enjoyment of the game for the players of the Begging class!  We shouldn't have to deal with such things, since we come into Norrath to get away from stress like that in the first place!<P>If you agree with the issues we bring out in this petition, please add your name to the list located at <a href="http://www.pitchinthebush.com">http://www.pitchinthebush.com</a>, and stand up to Verant and be heard!  Rogues and Warriors have been catered to, now it's our turn!  We have rights, too, and we're going to make sure Verant gives us what they owe us!!!<P>And before all you cold-hearted conservatives (you know who you are!) start mouthing off about our petition, I want to point out that all beggars are ROLEPLAYERS.  Yes, I have carefully considered my character's personality, and it's such that he constantly shouts "Can ne1 spare thy 100 plat for a lvl 10 char?  I was lag-killed and my corpse decayedeth with all my $$$!!!" so loud that everyone from Felwithe to Kelethin can hear it.  It's who he is, and that's how I play him!  Since it's a valid style, and since I'm a paying customer, you should be banned for thinking otherwise!<P>Thanks!!!<P>- Astam Ztunmun, The Oppressed<P>P.S. - Be sure to fill it out by mid-August, since I won't have any time to do this once school starts.  <P>Power, brother!!!

<!-- End Content -->
