<SPAN CLASS="credit">Author:</SPAN> 
<span class="credit2">Jythri  (<a href="mailto:N/A" class="credit2">N/A</a>)</SPAN>&nbsp;&nbsp;  
<SPAN CLASS="credit">Organization:</SPAN> <a href="http://www.soerbiard.com" class="credit2">Soerbiard</a><br>

<SPAN CLASS="regtext">
<!-- Begin Content -->
<P>
<i>Note: This was sung shortly after the ceremony of the marriage of Aranath and Syrah. It was sung by Jythri and Mystykyl.<br></i><br><br>Underneath Ro's soft and waning moon, A Northman found a radiant cause to swoon-- A bardess raptured shaman's heart with tune, So Aranath sought out kind Syrah's boon.<br><br>Few words he said, but his eyes spoke a tale Of love, which over Syrah did prevail. So waited he for time to come avail And bring her age to his; a long travail.<br><br>Aranath and Syrah, Shaman and Bard, Northman and Elf, Forever be paired.<br><br>When age was full and Syrah was then grown, Aranath did charm her for his own, Their fates entangled, bound them close as one, As they traversed from dawn to setting sun.<br><br>And on one timely day did shaman light His lovely Syrah to the air in flight. Aranath asked Syrah to requite His love with hers in marriage to his right.<br><br>Aranath and Syrah, Shaman and Bard, Northman and Elf, Forever be paired.<br><br>She answered from her soul and answered true That not another love but his would do. He took her in his arms and broght her to His tight embrace and held her all night through.<br><br>So happiness we call upon their life, To Aranath and Syrah, joy be rife! May goodly spirits keep your road from strife And give you many years as man and wife.<br><br>Aranath and Syrah, Shaman and Bard, Northman and Elf, Forever be paired.

