<img src="/images/topback.jpg" valign="bottom" width=475 height=2><br>
<SPAN CLASS="credit">Author:</SPAN> 
<span class="credit2">Shadoe  (<a href="mailto:shadoe@vaultnetwork.com" class="credit2">shadoe@vaultnetwork.com</a>)</SPAN>&nbsp;&nbsp;  
<SPAN CLASS="credit">Organization:</SPAN> <a href="http://www.eqvault.com" class="credit2">EQVault</a><br>

<SPAN CLASS="regtext">
<!-- Begin Content -->
<P>
<P>Fondest greetings to everyone!</P><P>Some of you may recognize me from my contributed rants at Gram's Place.  Others out there may recognize me as that guy you saw lying face-down in the gutter one bleak Monday morning.  Whatever the case, I am here to take the soapbox and tell you everything you ever wanted to know about female ogres, but were afraid to ask.</P><P>The female ogre is an oddly vivacious creature... much like a sprite or real-world valley girl.  The female ogre is rarely seen in in the world of Norrath, but it can be a truly breathtaking sight to see one flitting from flower to flower amidst the dew in the early morning air.  Never underestimate the portents of what may at first seem a minor earthquake beneath your feet... for it just might be the first signs that the elusive female ogre is frolicking nearby -- a sign that is surely one of omen.</P><P>Should you perchance stumble across such a scene of unabashed revelry, be sure not to approach too closely or call attention to yourself.  For, the female ogre is a most fickle creature, and will not hesitate to endulge in a bit of frolicking on your tiny, pathetic, earth-trodden body after she notices your eavesdropping.  Further, the raw brains of any non-ogrish creature is a most succulent delight to the female ogre, who would not hesitate to dine on one such as yourself, had she a mind to (pun intended).</P><P>Like most of the ogre species, female ogres harbor a tendency for violence.  This is particularly true when provoked by a creature of lesser stature -- which encompasses basically every other sentient being in Norrath.  Even the mighty dragonkind fear the female ogre during the infamous "groobergrog" season, which takes place every two- to seven hours, and lasts for at least a day.</P><P>But what is perhaps the most peculiar - and yet not widely known -- fact about the psyche of the female ogre is her innate ability to sing exactly one half note off-key with impunity while wailing her resounding mating call.</P><P>Above all, if you learn just one thing about the female ogre, be sure never EVER to call one "Helga" to her face.</P><P>Well, that's all the time we have for today.  Be sure to tune in next time when we study the table manners of troll kin.  Until then, safe wishes to you ogre-ogglers.</P><P>- &lt;Shadoe&gt;</P>

