<SPAN CLASS="pagesub">P.V.P. Player vs. Pimple </SPAN><br>
<img src="/images/topback.jpg" valign="bottom" width=475 height=2><br>
<SPAN CLASS="credit">Author:</SPAN> 
<span class="credit2">Shadoe  (<a href="mailto:shadoe@vaultnetwork.com" class="credit2">shadoe@vaultnetwork.com</a>)</SPAN>&nbsp;&nbsp;  
<SPAN CLASS="credit">Organization:</SPAN> <a href="http://www.eqvault.com" class="credit2">EQVault</a><br>

<SPAN CLASS="regtext">
<!-- Begin Content -->
<P>
I figured I might as well get this out of the way, since the topic of the PVP switch is apparently something that we as online gamers just can't get enough of.  After all, it's not as if this subject matter is a thoroughly dead, rotten, and skeletonized horse we're whipping.<P>Player versus player gaming.  On the surface it seems so simple... about as black and white as a smiling caricature of Sammy Davis Jr.  No biggie.... but wait!  Who might that figure be, who yonder approaches along the road?  "MoFo JaCkMaN l33t PiCkNoS bAdAsS."  What the bleedin' 'ell kind of name is...? *WHACK*  By the time you're done figuring out their name, you're toast!  Worse than that, you're a briquette!  Before long, you'll be smoldering in someone's hibachi somewhere.  And what does this MoFo do?  He picks your corpse clean and moves on without so much as an evil look.  Oh yeah, now that's roleplaying... in Bolivia, maybe!<P>Hence the purpose behind the creation of the PVP switch.  Those who'd rather avoid such a dubious fate are free to do so, if they like.  But wait, there's more!  If you act now, you can also play a character who can fight other like-minded player characters to the death, if that's what you'd rather do!  And that's not all!  Those PVP characters who are killed only lose <I>one</I> item, instead of being taken to the cleaners.  If RedEye included a free set of Ginsu knives, I would think the symmetry would make us all break into tears.  Preorder now, operators are standing by.<P>This is why I'm so completely floored at the raging firestorm of controversy this little solution has sparked off.  The only thing I can say this controversy has accomplished for certain is that it's allowed people to proudly display their IQs (or lack thereof) for the world to see.  Go to any message board with such a topic, and you can cleanly pick out those people who are wisely open-minded, and those who are begging for a cranial enema.<P>For those uninformed souls who don't hang out in the #eqvault channel on the DreamMyst IRC network, there's a petition -- yes, you read that right, a P-E-T...ition -- to get RedEye to open up a +PVP-only server.  This, naturally, has set off another explosion of opinion, and I'm here to go through each worthy argument one-by-one, as per my traditional fashion...<P>My references have come from various msg boards around the web. I'd name them all, but I'm lazy.<P>----------<P><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">Let em have their day in the sun. More pkrs go to this server, the less of em will go<BR>bother the RP'rs. I think it is a good idea even if they can't setup a server without the<BR>pvp switch, having one officially santioned would be a great thing.<BR>Arctander <BR>PB Gardens, FL USA - </FONT><P>I decided to start with this one because the logic behind it sounds really good at first.  But after fasting and praying to Innoruk for guidance, I'm thinking that it's not going to solve as much as one might suspect after all.  Don't get me wrong; I think the idea of herding the like-minded player types together is a fine idea.  But I have to ask myself, will a +PVP server alone accomplish this?<P>The powergamers should love it, as they've finally got a no-holds-barred playground in which to Quake themselves senseless; I say more power to them.  In this sense, I believe what Arctander says is quite valid.  <P>I also believe that powergamers (the mature ones, anyway) try to respect roleplayers' wishes and leave them alone whenever possible.  So someone please tell me what this will prevent...?<P>The KeWl DoOdZ are the ones I'm most concerned about.  In other words, powergamers (and let's not kid ourselves, they <I>are</I> a type of powergamer!) whose river of entertainment flows from the spring of deliberately making their fellow players' lives difficult, simply because they are totally anonymous in Norrath, and because they can.  This type of player won't be happy on a +PVP-only server because they only prey on the weak -- something your average powergamer typically is not.  So they'll migrate to the other servers in the hopes of finding the odd +PVP roleplayer to snub, anyway.<P><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">I think a pvp server is a good idea like was stated to really get good roleply i think it is<BR>needed, like how can lets say ogres are your enemy you storm their cmp but all are<BR>-pvp stupid there should be at least one server dedicated to pvp ing thanx<BR>Dave <BR>edmonton, ab Canada - </FONT><P>The "realism" roleplayers will make their token attempt at playing on such a server, but I predict most of them will eventually come to the conclusion that the immersion-shattering factor of playing with a bunch of powergamers who couldn't care less about world context far outweighs the factor of the odd -pvp character standing unharmed amidst a bloody camp raid.<P><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">Good Idea for a "Tempory" PKing fest... But I see UO all over again. alot of people<BR>being PK's and interupting the Fun people are trying to have.....Player vs Dungeons<BR>and what not. Now, for tempory fueds between say "Dark Elves and Humans/Elves<BR>have started to war across -so and so- contenent, that would be interesting... But after<BR>a week or something, it's over. But during that time, Dark Elves vs Humans/Elves is<BR>free game...<BR>Jacob D. <BR>Sterling, VA USA - </FONT><P>The occasional declaration of outright war between races idea is good, I think.  Although, it could lead to all sorts of confusion among the different players who'd rather not get into racial politics, or the odd-man-out type of characters like your "civilized" troll, per se.  Imagine logging in one day after a couple of weeks' hiatus and suddenly being killed by an enemy character when you thought you were safe as a -PVP.  I can see a lot of redundant sorting out to do for GMs when the victim starts to complain that the PVP switch isn't working right.<P><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">plz give us PvP!!! without pvp every game simply sucks!!<BR>Sebastian Dickgiesser <BR>Karlsruhe, germany - </FONT><P>Cranial enema.<P><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">We need PvP Server ! The relation PvP Players : PvE Only will be about 10 : 1<BR>Michael Vogt <BR>Hannover, Germany - </FONT><P>I'm thinking this guy's point is this: on your average server, the number of -PVP characters will so greatly outweigh +PVP characters, that good PVP combat will be difficult -- even frustrating -- to find.  Where he gets his ratio of 10:1, I can't say.  I'll give 20:1 odds he probably picked it out of the air.  <P>Me?  I'm willing to admit I haven't a clue what the ratio will be once EQ releases, but judging from what I'm hearing about the beta so far, he may have a point.<P>However, have any of you pk geniuses out there even considered having your own +PVP events?  If it's just too strenuous for you to find other players to whack, I think it would do a world of good if you actually organized something yourselves instead of sitting on your butts and whining for RedEye to do it for you.  On top of it all, I'm sure EQ Vault would be ecstatic to post the announcement for you without whining about it too much, and that way you get publicity for your style of playing.  Win/win situations don't come by too often, people...<P><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">Realism is RolePlaying....<BR>Andy Anderson <BR>Antioch, CA USA - </FONT><P>Realism is <I>not</I> roleplaying.  <I>Fantasy</I> is roleplaying, which is why we have dragons and magic, rather than jobs and taxes.  If you want realism to a better degree, go join your local chapter of the <A HREF="http://www.sca.org">Society for Creative Anachronism</A>.<P><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">I propose we make a server so those whining +pvp won't complain anymore. I am sick<BR>of hearing about people not being able to kill other players. Make a server for these<BR>anti-socials already and so they will leave us -pvp's alone. Why don't you name it the<BR>kEWldOOd kILLAZ server. <BR>Mendoza <BR>Washington, DC USA - </FONT><P>That's reason enough for me... but I have my doubts if that alone will cut it for RedEye.<P><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">I'm not in beta but it would convince me to purchase the game plus it would add to the<BR>danger or adventuring and allow many new roleplaying opportunities.<BR>By-Tor <BR>Centerville, In USA - </FONT><P>Wise and open-minded.  I don't <I>agree</I> with all of what he/she says, but they're being perfectly reasonable, civil, and most importantly, they're not whining!<P><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">I think the idea of a PVP shard is insane. If you want unfetered PVP go back to UO.<BR>You guys already ruined that game, don't ruin this. Let 989(Redeye) focus their<BR>attention on the MAJORITY of the paying public -PVP. If you want realism, live your<BR>life and stay out of our game!<BR>Overlord<BR>USA - </FONT><P>Man, who is THIS guy?  Me makes me frightened for my life... ;)<P><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">aehm....I have already said all what I can say to PvP...and the unnecessary Switch<BR>Ris Natar <BR>Wiesbaden, HE Germany - </FONT><P>Cranial enema... and a good therapist.<P><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">I think that it would be a good idea. 1.) A lot of people would stop complaining... 2.) It<BR>does ad an element of danger in the everyday life of gaining levels...:)<BR>Ryan Benton <BR>Modesto, ca USA - </FONT><P>Wise and open-minded.<P><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">i was gunna start a petition like this, but im just too lazy...and i want all servers to be<BR>pk-switch free, cept for 1 <BR>michael lambert <BR>vancouver, wa USA - </FONT><P>Okay, I'm taking this to mean that our esteemed Mr. Lambert believes there should be only one (1) server with the PVP switch enabled for the roleplayers.  In effect, a roleplay-only server.  <P>Talk about the world's WORST idea, and I'll tell you why.  The definition of what exactly constitutes "roleplaying" is such a highly subjective term, that the GMs would be spending more time weeding through the massive finger-pointing from roleplayers saying that "So-and-So isn't roleplaying," or "they got their name from a Robert Jordan novel," that the roleplayer's world would be self-shattering.  I'm tellin' you, if you think powergamers have made more than their fair share of whining, then hunney, you ain't seen nuttin' yet!<P><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">While I am not big on the stereo type of pking, player vs player interaction, done<BR>right, is a lot of fun. If a +pvp server is set in play, I would like to see the faction<BR>standards greatly increased compared to a standard server.<BR>Death Knight USA - </FONT><P>Another open-minded comment, and it's one I'd agree with if I didn't already think we had its equivalent on a regular server with the duelling concept.  I, for one, would be happy to roleplay my character as a victim of some dark ritual if accosted by a well played group.  To that end, I'd gladly make my character vulnerable to become their sacrifice by hitting the accept button when the executioner challenged me.  Of course, this is highly dependent on what I was doing at the moment... if I were busy, I'd probably decline.  But they can always find someone else, or I'd be glad to return at a later time.  To me, a good roleplay is worth the hit to your stats from death, and most roleplayers will allow you to keep the one item that would normally be looted.<P>My point is, one doesn't have to be +PVP to roleplay a proper death.<P><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">no comment... just make it happen. After 2 weeks of EverQuest I'm already bored out<BR>of my mind. "Hmm, what to do? I guess I'll go sit at a camp and wait for another skel<BR>to spawn"<BR>VehT <BR>Vancouver, WA USA - </FONT><P>I have no idea why this guy bothered to post anything.  He obviously wants someone to entertain him rather than being creative and doing it himself.  Oh, yes indeed... Mr. Enthusiasm here is definitely someone I'd want to play with, no question...<P><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">Thank you for coming and signing the petition. I have great hopes for this, and I hope<BR>to see every one on the PvP server!<BR>Nick Dawson (Phlashbak) <BR>Boulder City, NV USA - </FONT><P>Nick's keeping a positive attitude, which is refreshing to see among the people who want this server so desperately.<P>Do I support the idea of a +PVP server?  Well, personally, I don't think it could hurt to give it a shot and see what comes of it.  There's nothing written in stone that RedEye can't make it a regular server after a while, if it doesn't work out.<P>Do I think it will have the desired effect on the rest of the servers?  Some, but not tremendously.  <P>Did I sign the petition?  No, because it's something I'd rarely (if ever) use, and if they want their petition to hold any leverage with RedEye, it has to be genuine.  <P>One attitude I see about the PVP switch over and over is the sentiment that "RedEye/Sony is going to miss out on a lot of customers, and if they want to make a profit, they'd... blah, blah, blah."  Every time I see it, I have to ask myself what kind of arrogant yutz would say something like that and pit himself against a company that has proven itself to know how to consistently make money with PC games?  It blows me away how people profess to have all the answers.<P>Is there an answer to the gap that exists between powergamer and roleplayer?  If it exists, it isn't going to be discovered with the creation of just one game, no matter how good it is.  My opinion is that there are a ton of really good ideas out there that can help, and it will be a matter of evolution more than anything else that will bring about its discovery.  <P>What I don't abide is the attitude that somehow RedEye owes us this server, as if it were a community service that they allow us to play <I>our</I> way.  Hey, if you don't like something, don't play it.  Take it a step further and don't cajole yourself into <I>paying</I> for it.  It's how our economy works, and it's that simple.  <P>And hey, if you think you can put together a better game and make more money than any existing game company, then by all means do it.  Put your money where your mouth is, and who knows?  It may turn out you were right after all...<P>- &lt;Shadoe&gt;

